1
00:00:01,126 --> 00:00:02,502
[countdown playing]

2
00:00:02,585 --> 00:00:04,504
[light music playing]

3
00:00:04,587 --> 00:00:07,674
BINI Chapter 3: Jhoanna Take 1.

4
00:00:07,757 --> 00:00:11,636
- [thrilling music playing]
- [laughter]

5
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:14,931
BINI Chapter 3: Aiah Take 1.

6
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:17,475
- [thrilling music continues]
- [squealing]

7
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:19,728
BINI Chapter 3: Gwen Take 1.

8
00:00:19,811 --> 00:00:21,896
[loud cheer]

9
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:24,816
BINI Chapter 3: BINI Stacey Take 1.

10
00:00:24,899 --> 00:00:26,776
[thrilling music continues]

11
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:29,279
[hissing, humming]

12
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:30,864
Scene 1-- Oops.

13
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:32,198
- [staff] It's "take one."
- [laughter]

14
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:33,199
- Go on.
- Alright.

15
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,827
BINI Mikha Chapter 3...

16
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:37,162
Take 1.

17
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:38,288
- [snaps]
- [Mikha] Action.

18
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:41,916
[thrilling music continues]

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,753
BINI Chapter 3: Colet Take 1.

20
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:46,713
[thrilling music continues]

21
00:00:46,796 --> 00:00:48,631
[growls]

22
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:51,384
BINI Chapter 3: Maloi Take 1.

23
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:52,343
[snaps]

24
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:55,221
- Hey!
- Hey!

25
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:57,057
Will there be more takes?

26
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,266
[all chuckling]

27
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:03,146
- BINI Chapter 3, Sheena Take 1!
- [snaps]

28
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:05,732
[thunder rolling]

29
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:08,443
[muffled voices]
<i>After thirty days of BINIverse,</i>

30
00:01:08,526 --> 00:01:09,694
<i>we move to regionals.</i>

31
00:01:09,778 --> 00:01:13,281
<i>Are you ready for Canada and the US?</i>

32
00:01:13,364 --> 00:01:14,699
<i>Yes, of course!</i>

33
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,619
<i>We're ready but of
course, it'll be more difficult.</i>

34
00:01:17,702 --> 00:01:24,167
["Huwag Muna Tayong Umuwi" playing]

35
00:01:39,724 --> 00:01:46,731
["Huwag Muna Tayong Umuwi" continues]

36
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:55,031
Oh, you guys are here already.

37
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,449
Wow. [chuckles]

38
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:57,951
It's early.

39
00:01:58,493 --> 00:02:00,954
- Hi, Director!
- [director] Hello.

40
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:03,331
Hi, Blooms. We are here!

41
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:05,583
Hello!

42
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,710
I'm tired! [chuckles]

43
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:08,795
[laughs]

44
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:11,589
It was only our second time in the US,

45
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:12,507
but we were happy

46
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:14,717
because even as soon
as we reached the airport,

47
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:18,012
we didn't expect
that people would recognize us.

48
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:19,764
[cameraman] Ready? One, two, three...

49
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,391
- Eyes here.
- [camera shutter clicking]

50
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:26,396
After the regionals,
we prepared for the LA tour.

51
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,856
The flight was organized by batch.

52
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:30,316
Why were we the first ones to fly?

53
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,985
Ah, right, because we're older.

54
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:35,947
[p.a. Announcer speaking indistinctly]

55
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,657
[man] Take care.

56
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:39,701
The batch one were the older members.

57
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:44,080
The last batch were the younger members,
me, Mikha, and Jhoanna.

58
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:45,456
Ah, right.

59
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:47,417
Yes, we got there first.

60
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,751
Why did we get there first?

61
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,795
Why did we split into groups?

62
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:52,213
[staff] You changed flights.

63
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:53,423
There was a typhoon!

64
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:55,049
Right. Okay.

65
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:56,593
We're only five now.

66
00:02:56,676 --> 00:02:58,052
[staff] How was your flight?

67
00:02:58,136 --> 00:02:59,095
It was okay.

68
00:02:59,178 --> 00:03:01,472
It was our first time
flying business class.

69
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:02,974
We really enjoyed it! [chuckles]

70
00:03:03,057 --> 00:03:07,937
It was our first time
flying business class together for work.

71
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:10,440
I didn't hold back.
I ate all the offered food.

72
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:12,609
They were like,
"You want dessert or something?"

73
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:14,360
It felt like a dream.

74
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:17,322
I used to just watch
Blackpink flying business class.

75
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:19,073
Now, it's BINI. Like, wow, who are we?

76
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:20,909
Oh, shucks. Things have really changed.

77
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:26,623
That's where we made up for all the sleep
we missed back in the Philippines.

78
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:29,959
We're on the way to our AIRBNB.

79
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:32,170
[suspenseful music playing]

80
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:37,342
[Colet] By the time we got to the airport,
we thought Jhoanna was pulling a prank.

81
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:41,971
We were about to check in
when Jhoanna suddenly felt dizzy.

82
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:42,931
I told Sheena,

83
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:44,557
"Shee, I feel like something hit me."

84
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:48,728
I mean, everything suddenly felt off.

85
00:03:48,811 --> 00:03:53,316
I sat down, gripping my suitcase.
I was like, "I can't take this anymore."

86
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:56,486
[engine humming]

87
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:59,197
[Gwen] At first,
they kept updating the group chat.

88
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,531
It was very sudden.

89
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:03,409
Jho was still fine, joking with Sheena.

90
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:05,411
Then just as I turned around...

91
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:06,496
She went down like that.

92
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:08,289
Good thing someone beside her caught her.

93
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,333
Something bad really happened to her.

94
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:13,336
Of course, we got worried,
especially since we weren't there for her.

95
00:04:13,419 --> 00:04:17,590
[Anna] Is someone taking
over the choreography or what?

96
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:19,926
[Machu] I think it should be Maloi.

97
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:21,886
[Jhoanna] Until
they took me to the hospital.

98
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:24,389
That's when they told
me I needed to be admitted.

99
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:26,516
I was crying in the emergency room.

100
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:28,726
And I said, "Miss MQ, I can still fly."

101
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:32,522
That's when we heard
that Jhoanna couldn't make it.

102
00:04:32,605 --> 00:04:34,607
We were unsure if
she would be able to catch up.

103
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:38,403
When that happened,
I asked, "Lord, why am I here?"

104
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:45,410
[thriller music playing]

105
00:04:45,493 --> 00:04:47,704
[train engine rumbling]

106
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:52,333
[upbeat music playing]

107
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:53,251
Wow.

108
00:04:53,334 --> 00:05:00,300
[upbeat music continues]

109
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:03,553
Hold on.

110
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:07,098
We can survive this.

111
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:09,642
[Jonathan] there will come a point

112
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:12,186
when you'll saturate the local market.

113
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:15,148
They really made it to the top.

114
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:20,570
And what do you do with all
that clout and success you've earned?

115
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:24,240
The next step for
growth is to go international.

116
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:26,701
[cameraman] Sorry, one more.

117
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:28,411
- [chuckling]
- I accidentally covered it.

118
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:30,079
One, two, three...

119
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:33,374
- [light music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

120
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:38,254
[overlapping chatter]

121
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:42,300
It's like all my hard work just vanished.

122
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:44,093
I really went all out. [chuckles softly]

123
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:45,762
[faint chatter, chuckling]

124
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:48,097
- Money's gone.
- [laughter]

125
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:50,099
[Aiah] There's bread.

126
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:51,392
I don't like that.

127
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:54,687
[Stacey] It was so nice
to feel that sisterhood again.

128
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:56,355
We're not always together now.

129
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:58,483
It felt like the first
time in a long while

130
00:05:58,566 --> 00:06:00,151
we got to do things

131
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:01,986
like grocery shopping
and having sleepovers.

132
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:02,904
What's yours?

133
00:06:02,987 --> 00:06:05,031
Coffee? [laughing]

134
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:06,783
I want to go back to the Philippines now.

135
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:07,992
- [fake crying]
- [chuckles]

136
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:10,119
U-S-A.

137
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:11,162
I love the Philippines.

138
00:06:11,245 --> 00:06:14,290
But during that time, I developed anxiety.

139
00:06:14,373 --> 00:06:19,337
So, I just really looked
forward to stepping out from here.

140
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:22,465
To be somewhere
I could walk around freely again,

141
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:23,925
even go jogging without worry.

142
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:25,718
I have a video of him saying...

143
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:30,056
[in deep voice] "Girls,
whose charger is this?"

144
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:31,474
- That charger!
- It's Aiah's!

145
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:32,725
- [laughter]
- It's not mine!

146
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:33,726
It's not yours?

147
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,144
[Maloi] "Whose charger is this?"

148
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,562
"Whose charger is this?"

149
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:38,314
- [makes noises]
- "Whose charger is this?"

150
00:06:38,397 --> 00:06:40,983
[Gwen] I have lots of videos of that too.

151
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,819
We love Coach Mickey. We miss him so much.

152
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:43,820
But he barely shows up.

153
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,113
[chuckles]

154
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:47,573
2024 was obviously a roller coaster.

155
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:49,200
When we started working with the girls,

156
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:51,953
we tried to prepare
them for a lot of things.

157
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:55,123
We tried to prepare
them for what might happen.

158
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:56,916
But everything happened so fast.

159
00:06:56,999 --> 00:06:58,167
Come on, look.

160
00:06:59,418 --> 00:07:00,795
This is next level.

161
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:06,092
It's so high-tech. [chuckles]

162
00:07:06,175 --> 00:07:10,555
[indistinct chatter]

163
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:11,806
Oh.

164
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:13,474
Here's more.

165
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:17,186
[somber music playing]

166
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:20,356
[Mickey] There were so
many voices and so much attention.

167
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,483
Who do you trust?

168
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,318
What should you listen to?

169
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:26,362
How do you deal with the pressure?

170
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:29,240
It was changing fast, and it was scary.

171
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:32,034
[Aiah] We weren't
used to Jho not being there.

172
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,870
It felt so different without her.

173
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:38,374
[somber music continues]

174
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:42,545
But we were already there,
so we had to keep going.

175
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,714
And Jhoanna would just catch up later.

176
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:49,218
Of course, it felt like going
through a serious heartbreak.

177
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:50,636
[laughs]

178
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:55,725
We weren't even sure if
Sheena and Mikha would make it.

179
00:07:55,808 --> 00:08:02,773
- [airplane rumbling]
- [thrilling music playing]

180
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:07,028
[Lauren] I think we're
the first Filipino act to appear in KCON.

181
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:08,362
So through that,

182
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:11,532
through the marketing
efforts of Star Events and Star Music,

183
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:13,659
we got into KCON.

184
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:16,287
- Thank you.
- [Mikha] You guys are here?

185
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:19,457
- You're here! Hello!
- Hello! Aww!

186
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:22,919
[Sheena] It's sad because we were the
first-ever P-Pop group to perform at KCON.

187
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:26,714
It was such a huge
event and opportunity for us.

188
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:28,841
We felt so lost without Jhoanna.

189
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,801
[upbeat music playing]

190
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,845
Bye, thanks!

191
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:36,516
[Mikha] Oh, my god! The house is big.

192
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:37,808
Hello!

193
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,144
- Oh, my god!
- [laughter]

194
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,772
This is your room, Sheena and Mikha.

195
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:44,565
[chuckling]

196
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:45,733
[Mikha] We weren't used to it.

197
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:47,985
It's weird not having your leader around.

198
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:50,446
- Have you guys slept?
- Yes, we just woke up.

199
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:52,657
That's our problem.
You might not get any sleep later.

200
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,450
[Lauren] Of course, I panicked.

201
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:56,202
Not because she couldn't perform,

202
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,246
but because I was more
worried about her condition.

203
00:08:58,329 --> 00:08:59,413
Because they said it was...

204
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:01,749
- [Lauren] UTI.
- Jho has UTI?

205
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:03,501
[Lauren] She rarely
drinks water, that's why.

206
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:04,877
Keep that in mind.

207
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:06,754
The test result says she has UTI?

208
00:09:06,837 --> 00:09:10,216
So far, she still needs
to undergo a lot of tests.

209
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:13,177
All the girls would have to
make an adjustment because,

210
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:15,930
from an eight-girl
performance, it came down to seven.

211
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:16,889
And that wasn't easy.

212
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:22,562
[overlapping chatter]

213
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:26,232
- Group photo.
- Nice.

214
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:28,359
Okay, let's make Jhoanna jealous.

215
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:29,569
[Maloi] We had a missing piece.

216
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:32,822
It's like we couldn't
stand properly without her.

217
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:37,159
We struggled while she wasn't around,
trying to figure out who would stand where

218
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,619
and who would do what.

219
00:09:38,703 --> 00:09:39,996
How many of this should we order?

220
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:41,163
Who else wants milkshake?

221
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:43,332
Who wants a burger? You guys can share.

222
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,417
[Colet] Wait a second.

223
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,585
Get four, so they can have some too.

224
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:48,296
Just that, Sheena, Jhoanna, oh, Stacks.
Yeah, right.

225
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:52,091
[Colet] Goodness,
Jhoanna is really the one leading BINI.

226
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:55,469
She usually speaks on behalf of the group.

227
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:58,097
Since Jhoanna wouldn't
make it, we had to re-block.

228
00:09:58,180 --> 00:10:00,683
- Move backwards.
- Who'll be at the center?

229
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,143
One more.

230
00:10:02,226 --> 00:10:03,936
You can't see
the gaps at the back anymore.

231
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:04,979
They're not noticeable.

232
00:10:05,062 --> 00:10:07,189
[Maloi] 360? So it's visible?

233
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:10,067
[Sheena] Oh, this is a 360.

234
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:13,112
[Aiah] That's also my formation,
then she'll push the other two.

235
00:10:13,195 --> 00:10:14,655
Then on my side is Jho.

236
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:15,823
Who's going to sing? She's supposed to.

237
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:18,159
I think we need to
adjust the blocking here.

238
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:19,493
This block here?

239
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:20,953
This one.

240
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:23,914
[singing "Cherry On Top" by BINI]

241
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,249
[Mickey] You need to understand

242
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,960
that wherever we go
or whatever we're doing,

243
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,128
we still have a long way to go,

244
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:32,173
so we have to work
hard to climb the ladder.

245
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:33,424
- Eyy!
- Eyy!

246
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:36,052
- [Mickey] You learn fast!
- [laughter]

247
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:40,473
[upbeat music playing]

248
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:44,018
- That's right.
- Okay, that's good.

249
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:45,478
Let's try it from the top.

250
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:47,146
- Come on.
- Turn on the music.

251
00:10:47,229 --> 00:10:48,773
So it's fine that Jho's not around.

252
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:50,566
- We can manage.
- [chuckling]

253
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,943
- We can do this.
- It seems easy, right?

254
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,945
At the end of the day,
because they were eight

255
00:10:55,029 --> 00:10:56,530
and all together as a group,

256
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,240
they should act like a family.

257
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,617
If a member goes through something,

258
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,243
they just have to
learn how to deal with it.

259
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:07,500
[instrumental music playing]

260
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:11,087
It's a good starting point
because it's not just for Filipinos.

261
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:17,134
It's for a mixed audience
who appreciates Asian music.

262
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:19,261
To be on that stage

263
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:23,349
and to be performing
alongside other groups...

264
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:25,851
It's definitely a huge boost for us.

265
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:29,522
[thrilling music playing]

266
00:11:29,605 --> 00:11:34,819
[loud cheering]

267
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:36,570
[audience] Whoo!

268
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:40,533
[faint chatter]

269
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:45,454
[upbeat music playing]

270
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:48,124
[Machu] In Team BINI,
you don't just carry one title.

271
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:50,459
As a coach, you need to know how to sew,

272
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:53,254
you need to know how to give massages.

273
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:55,089
Everything. Oh, goodness.

274
00:11:55,172 --> 00:11:56,590
All Team BINI members are talented.

275
00:11:56,674 --> 00:11:59,468
[upbeat music continues then stops]

276
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:02,721
[Colet] It's a lot of
pressure every time I listen to OPM

277
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:07,143
or Filipino talents being
introduced on the global stage.

278
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:10,354
But we're just doing
what we've always done.

279
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,356
It's like we haven't really changed.

280
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:15,943
Lord, thank You for
this day You've given us.

281
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:19,029
Thank You for
bringing us safely here to LA.

282
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:22,992
[Gwen] The preparation in
the Philippines took a long time.

283
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:26,245
Now for global domination,

284
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:29,623
we're still finding
our way and working on it.

285
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,375
[Sheena] Coach Mach.

286
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:32,835
- Go.
- Oh, my god.

287
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:34,628
- [chuckles]
- Let's go!

288
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:36,714
- Go for it.
- Ouch.

289
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:37,923
Ouch.

290
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:43,846
- [hands clapping]
- [chuckling]

291
00:12:43,929 --> 00:12:45,264
Ouch.

292
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,641
[engine revving]

293
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:49,477
[Aiah] We were actually really nervous

294
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:53,063
because most of
the people there were K-pop artists.

295
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:55,107
And it felt like
we were the only P-pop group.

296
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:59,528
We were worried about
what if people didn't know us,

297
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,530
what if they didn't like us,

298
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:03,532
and what if we faced a black ocean

299
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:07,036
where no one lit their light sticks,

300
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:09,538
didn't cheer, and just sat quietly.

301
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:10,664
Five, six, seven, eight, nine, go.

302
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:11,665
Two, three...

303
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:12,833
<i>- Long live!
- Long live!</i>

304
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,543
- Hi, I'm Aiah!
- I'm Colet.

305
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,837
- Hi, I'm Maloi.
- I'm Gwen.

306
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,130
- I'm Stacey.
- I'm Mikha.

307
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:19,131
I'm Sheena.

308
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:20,758
[all] And we are BINI!

309
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:21,800
From the Philippines!

310
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:22,843
Oh, right.

311
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:25,262
Just continue.
And we're from the Philippines.

312
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:27,765
- Alright, one more.
- And we are...

313
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:30,059
Sheena will speak first. After that...

314
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:31,101
Hi, I'm Sheena.

315
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:32,019
[all] And we are...

316
00:13:32,102 --> 00:13:35,940
- BINI from the Philippines!
- [loud cheering, applauding]

317
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:39,235
[Gwen] Never in my whole
life did I think I'd get to perform.

318
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:40,819
It felt impossible before.

319
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:44,073
All we ever dreamed of
was to do a mall show, right?

320
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:51,080
["Cherry On Top" by BINI playing]

321
00:13:51,163 --> 00:13:58,087
[audience cheering, applauding]

322
00:13:58,170 --> 00:14:05,177
["Cherry On Top" continues]

323
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:13,519
[Stacey] The fans
didn't just come for K-pop.

324
00:14:13,602 --> 00:14:14,645
They were also there for BINI.

325
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:16,188
They cheered for us too.

326
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:18,899
They didn't give us a black ocean.

327
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:21,819
Give it up one more time for BINI!

328
00:14:21,902 --> 00:14:23,571
[loud cheering, applauding]

329
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:25,197
[Sheena] Our performance was a free show

330
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:26,949
and not part of the main show.

331
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:29,577
But wow, the cheer was so loud!

332
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,871
And we found out there
were a lot of Filipinos there.

333
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:33,622
A lot of them came.

334
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:37,626
[squealing, cheering]

335
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,253
[audience member] Maloi, I love you!

336
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:40,212
Oh my gosh, wow.

337
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,463
It's really a dream come true.

338
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:45,259
As a K-pop fan, I'm so happy at KCON

339
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:47,219
because the K-pop groups

340
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:51,599
I used to idolize and
watch on TikTok were there.

341
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,934
[Aiah] Wow,
I used to just watch them in videos

342
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:54,977
or hear their songs.

343
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:57,396
And we finally met them.

344
00:14:57,479 --> 00:14:58,939
It felt so surreal.

345
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:01,859
[upbeat music playing]

346
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,360
[screams] We were really like that.

347
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:05,154
Of course, we had to be professional.

348
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:08,282
But behind closed doors,
I was totally smitten.

349
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:09,617
It was just me and Colet.

350
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,785
Then at the last minute, they told us,

351
00:15:11,869 --> 00:15:14,747
"Girls, they allowed
three members from BINI."

352
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:16,832
And Stacku quickly raised her hand, "Me!"

353
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:19,126
Guys, I'm going for it.
This only happens once.

354
00:15:19,209 --> 00:15:20,836
The opportunity knocks just once.

355
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:24,924
So, I really grabbed
it and didn't want to miss out

356
00:15:25,007 --> 00:15:26,884
because I've been
watching them for so long.

357
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:29,803
- Hello!
- BINI!

358
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:33,599
[Maloi] Oh my gosh! You look so good!

359
00:15:33,682 --> 00:15:34,767
[fan] Hi, Mikha!

360
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,851
Hi there!

361
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:36,894
Hi, Maloi!

362
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:40,314
Come on, let's take pictures!

363
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,816
We already saw foreigners so I said,

364
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:46,028
"Wow, so they really like our songs?"
It's amazing.

365
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:49,782
Did you get that? That <i>Pantropiko</i> outfit?

366
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:51,867
- Huh? Yeah.
- Of the girl.

367
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:52,868
[giggles]

368
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:55,704
[woman] Colet,
can I get a picture, please?

369
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:58,165
[Maloi] <i>With the help of
our fans and management,</i>

370
00:15:58,248 --> 00:16:00,000
<i>we're really starting to
get recognized, little by little.</i>

371
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,294
And our experience at KCON

372
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:06,507
is hands down one of
the highlights in BINI's journey

373
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:07,967
this 2024.

374
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:10,135
- You're beautiful!
- Thank you!

375
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:11,845
Thank you!

376
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,140
So far.

377
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:18,310
[Stacey] <i>After KCON,</i>

378
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:19,937
<i>we were looking for our service,</i>

379
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:22,439
<i>but we were told
it couldn't go into that area.</i>

380
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:25,567
So, what we did was
we walked a really long distance.

381
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,861
From Tomas Morato, to EDSA, to Cubao.

382
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:29,238
That was like the distance we walked.

383
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,281
This is part of our bonding.

384
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:33,367
No, we're helping the driver.

385
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:35,411
We don't want him to get
tired, so we'll approach him.

386
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,287
We're the service for the driver,

387
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:38,330
not the other way around.

388
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:44,086
It’s a very humbling feeling,
like going back to day one,

389
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:46,046
when no one knows you.

390
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:48,465
But it’s great because, in a way,

391
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:49,675
it gives you a fresh start.

392
00:16:49,758 --> 00:16:56,724
We're now seeing
the evacuees from the Crypto Arena.

393
00:16:57,099 --> 00:16:59,852
These are
the evacuees from the Crypto Arena.

394
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:01,145
Where is the service?

395
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:02,855
[laughter]

396
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,232
- Where...
- [woman] Are you guys BINI?

397
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:07,067
- Yes!
- [squealing]

398
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,986
We came all the way
from Canada! [chuckles]

399
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:10,362
[Maloi] It's your lucky day!

400
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:12,865
- Can we take a picture?
- Sure!

401
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:15,075
[woman] Aren't
you going to Canada on August 9?

402
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:16,118
Yes! Are you going to watch?

403
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:17,077
- Of course!
- Hopefully!

404
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:18,954
But your tickets are already sold out.

405
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:20,456
- Ow!
- That's how...

406
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:21,832
[Maloi] Let’s take a picture.

407
00:17:21,915 --> 00:17:26,128
[gentle music playing]

408
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:28,297
[Stacey] <i>We're not
used to this because, of course,</i>

409
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,298
<i>that’s another country.</i>

410
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:31,467
<i>We really expected
that we wouldn't be recognized,</i>

411
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:33,093
but we're so happy that at least,

412
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:36,638
even if just one person knows us,

413
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:38,932
our hearts are already so happy.

414
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:45,939
[woman shrieks]

415
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:48,650
Hi! We love you!

416
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:51,445
(In Bisaya) Come here, until the concert.

417
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,405
[IVY] <i>I can't, I have school.</i>

418
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,908
- Oh, come on.
- [girl] <i>Ma! Ma!</i>

419
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:01,080
[Colet] <i>All the first
times we experience in life,</i>

420
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:03,248
we should really be complete.

421
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:07,461
But of course,
there are things that can't be avoided.

422
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:09,213
It has become our inside joke,

423
00:18:09,296 --> 00:18:10,506
“Oh, Jhoanna's not here,”

424
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:13,050
but deep down, we're really sad.

425
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:18,138
[indistinct chatter, p.a. announcement]

426
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:24,978
[laughing]

427
00:18:27,689 --> 00:18:29,108
- Bye bye!
- Bye bye!

428
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:30,818
Bye!

429
00:18:32,152 --> 00:18:35,614
- Why?
- Uh, can I...

430
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:37,866
[quizzical music playing]

431
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:41,120
[Lauren] <i>Going to America,
we take on a different strategy.</i>

432
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,330
<i>We can't go there and</i>

433
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:44,915
pretend to know the market.

434
00:18:44,998 --> 00:18:47,709
- I thought it was just us?
- I thought it was casual?

435
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,419
- I thought it was just us.
- I thought she's just on live.

436
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:53,048
Show your goofy side,
so you girls can be funny.

437
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,716
But in English.

438
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,260
That’s also the worry of the other girls,

439
00:18:56,343 --> 00:18:58,345
they're saying they're
not used to speaking English.

440
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:01,140
[laughs] Oh my gosh!

441
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:05,185
I feel like, us girls,
we've improved in speaking in English.

442
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:06,979
But good thing we have
our strong representatives,

443
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:08,480
Aiah and Mikha.

444
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,566
- Ready, guys?
- Ready?

445
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:12,901
Anytime now.

446
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:15,279
[mimics drum roll, fanfare]

447
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:17,406
- [crowd roaring]
- [host] <i>What's up?</i>

448
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:18,699
<i>How are you guys doing today?</i>

449
00:19:18,782 --> 00:19:21,952
Humor in Tagalog is like,
you say it in Tagalog.

450
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:22,911
It’s super funny.

451
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:26,999
But if you translate it to
your American friend or something,

452
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,126
they won't laugh.

453
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,794
[host] <i>BINI!</i>

454
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:33,839
[crowd cheers]

455
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:38,969
[lively music playing]

456
00:19:39,052 --> 00:19:40,637
Thank you!

457
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,806
[crowd cheers]

458
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:43,891
Yes, we get it!

459
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:45,392
[laughter]

460
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:47,644
- Yeah...
- [HOST] Yeah, alright.

461
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,146
It’s really hard to explain.

462
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:50,439
[Maloi] <i>In that whole interview,</i>

463
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:53,066
<i>we only spoke in English.</i>

464
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:54,610
I was laughing at ourselves.

465
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:57,112
We can joke even in English?

466
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,530
Hmm, watch this!

467
00:19:58,614 --> 00:19:59,448
[laughs]

468
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:00,657
[interviewer] My question is,

469
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:02,910
if you are to switch
with one of your members,

470
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,077
who would it be and why?

471
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:05,120
Switch places?

472
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:06,788
[crowd laughs]

473
00:20:06,872 --> 00:20:09,124
[Sheena] <i>I'm so fluent in English now.</i>

474
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:12,085
So the conversation just flows smoothly,

475
00:20:12,169 --> 00:20:14,463
so the nervousness went away.
It was only at the beginning.

476
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:16,048
I'll hold your leg up.

477
00:20:16,131 --> 00:20:18,592
[giggling, laughing]

478
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:23,180
[upbeat music playing]

479
00:20:23,263 --> 00:20:25,182
[laughing]

480
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:28,602
["Cherry On Top" plays]

481
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:32,314
- Okay!
- Thank you.

482
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:33,565
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

483
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:34,691
Thank you for coming!

484
00:20:35,776 --> 00:20:37,861
It feels like
I worked out for three hours.

485
00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:41,281
Oh my, our content shoots. [laughs]

486
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:42,824
We ran out of battery. [laughs]

487
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,701
If Gwen’s battery ran out, I was next.

488
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:45,911
[laughs]

489
00:20:45,994 --> 00:20:49,164
The things we went through...
The whole day we were...

490
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:55,212
[upbeat music continues]

491
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:56,296
- Ah.
- Good afternoon!

492
00:20:57,464 --> 00:20:58,757
Good morning!

493
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,093
After he said that, everyone agrees like,

494
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:02,594
"Oh my god, that’s a great idea!"

495
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:06,515
[laughs]

496
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:11,770
[upbeat music continues]

497
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:13,605
Ready? One, two...

498
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,899
[indistinct chatter]

499
00:21:15,983 --> 00:21:18,110
Wait, I'm going to quit.
Just kidding. [laughs]

500
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:25,617
[soft music playing]

501
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:27,369
[exhales]

502
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:32,541
[Gwen] <i>I didn't really see myself</i>

503
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:35,961
<i>going into this industry and this track.</i>

504
00:21:36,044 --> 00:21:39,673
So I'm slowly
adjusting to what’s happening.

505
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:44,094
[Aiah] <i>I enjoyed it.
But I did see others thinking,</i>

506
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:46,638
[gasps] "What is this
again?" Something like that.

507
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:50,934
I get it, we all have
different levels of energy.

508
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,105
[Stacey] <i>It’s really hard for us</i>

509
00:21:55,188 --> 00:21:57,983
to fake that you're really happy.

510
00:21:58,066 --> 00:21:59,860
You can't hide if you're tired.

511
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:01,820
Your face really shows it,

512
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:04,281
but of course, we're in the industry,

513
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:06,908
so you really need to push yourself.

514
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:10,120
And the things
that truly make us happy are food.

515
00:22:10,203 --> 00:22:12,998
- [diners chattering]
- [utensils clinking]

516
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,252
[Maloi] <i>I can't believe the scheduling.</i>

517
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:20,964
In one day,
there are like three or four schedules.

518
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:23,759
I can't imagine how it’s
possible to happen in one day.

519
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:25,385
It felt like we were in LA forever

520
00:22:25,469 --> 00:22:27,429
because of how much we did.

521
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:30,724
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

522
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:35,771
[chattering]

523
00:22:37,564 --> 00:22:38,857
[Sheena] <i>Even though it was non-stop,</i>

524
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:40,358
<i>we were just happy, us girls.</i>

525
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:43,779
Of course, we also
wanted the videos to turn out great.

526
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:47,282
We know we'll be
reaching different audiences.

527
00:22:47,365 --> 00:22:49,826
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

528
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:51,203
Bye!

529
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:55,791
[Aiah] <i>I think we also needed that time,</i>

530
00:22:55,874 --> 00:22:57,209
that break.

531
00:22:57,292 --> 00:22:58,752
Even though we were there for work,

532
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:01,338
it felt like work and play for me. Yeah.

533
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,383
Don't move anymore!

534
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:06,802
The battery is about to die!

535
00:23:07,385 --> 00:23:10,013
- Yay!
- Yay!

536
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:11,723
[reel rolling]

537
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:15,894
[Colet] <i>Even though
we were completely drained after that,</i>

538
00:23:15,977 --> 00:23:18,605
<i>we could still see the importance</i>

539
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:20,899
of that collaboration for BINI,

540
00:23:20,982 --> 00:23:22,609
because that’s one of the steps

541
00:23:22,692 --> 00:23:25,153
to getting BINI
recognized on the international stage.

542
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:31,576
- Thank you!
- Thank you! Thank you!

543
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:39,459
[Lauren] <i>It’s like day zero again.</i>

544
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:41,086
<i>When you get to America,</i>

545
00:23:41,169 --> 00:23:42,879
<i>there are millions and millions of artists</i>

546
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,714
<i>who want to penetrate Hollywood.</i>

547
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:48,677
The real measure of
success for an international career

548
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,054
is being able to penetrate the US.

549
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:55,350
[indistinct chatter]

550
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:59,229
[Jonathan]
What BINI is doing is very important

551
00:23:59,312 --> 00:24:01,064
for the Filipino music industry.

552
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:03,483
If BINI makes it to the global stage

553
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:05,193
and reaches a wider audience,

554
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:08,697
gets global recognition,

555
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:09,823
it will benefit us.

556
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:13,201
People around the world will get curious.

557
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,995
They will see that BINI is a great group,

558
00:24:15,078 --> 00:24:18,206
so, there must be
more artists in the Philippines

559
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:21,501
of the same caliber
waiting to be discovered.

560
00:24:21,585 --> 00:24:24,171
[airplane engine roaring]

561
00:24:30,343 --> 00:24:32,053
- [staff] How are you, Jho?
- [giggles]

562
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:35,307
Okay? Am I okay?

563
00:24:36,057 --> 00:24:36,892
I am okay.

564
00:24:36,975 --> 00:24:38,727
Wow, she's back!

565
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:41,188
- Hello!
- Gwen's not responding.

566
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:42,522
Hello, what's your name?

567
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:44,232
- [Jhoanna] I'm Jhoanna.
- [Aiah giggles]

568
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:46,109
Hello, I'm Joan.

569
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:48,737
[squeals] Jho!

570
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,655
Did your chin get longer?

571
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:52,699
My face got longer.

572
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:54,993
Just kidding. I missed you.

573
00:24:55,076 --> 00:24:56,369
I was only gone for five days,

574
00:24:56,453 --> 00:24:58,830
but I feel like I missed a lot already.

575
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:02,667
When I arrived, the girls were glowing.

576
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:05,378
They could pass as locals. [chuckles]

577
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:07,172
We can't be friends anymore.

578
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:09,758
We have American humor now.

579
00:25:09,841 --> 00:25:11,218
[laughs]

580
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:16,640
[upbeat music playing]

581
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:19,142
[indistinct chatter]

582
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:20,769
Did you miss me?

583
00:25:20,852 --> 00:25:22,270
Yeah.

584
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:25,649
How dare you.

585
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:27,234
Do you know what happened?

586
00:25:27,317 --> 00:25:30,904
You say the word "blond" differently now.

587
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:35,825
[chanting] BINI! BINI! BINI!

588
00:25:35,909 --> 00:25:38,703
- Hi!
- Hello!

589
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:42,457
- [chanting continues]
- [screaming]

590
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:47,712
[Aiah] It was so heartwarming.

591
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:51,341
Most of the second
generation of Filipinos here

592
00:25:51,424 --> 00:25:54,094
weren't born in the Philippines,

593
00:25:54,177 --> 00:25:56,388
but they know our songs.

594
00:25:56,471 --> 00:25:57,806
I'm BINI Louise.

595
00:25:57,889 --> 00:26:00,725
So my question is,
I came all the way from Seattle...

596
00:26:00,809 --> 00:26:02,644
- Wow!
- [claps]

597
00:26:02,727 --> 00:26:07,357
[Maloi] There were Blooms
who came from different states.

598
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:13,613
We were amazed
that we have fans everywhere.

599
00:26:13,697 --> 00:26:16,157
[woman] One, two, three, smile!

600
00:26:17,325 --> 00:26:19,119
[Sheena] Hi, thank you!

601
00:26:19,202 --> 00:26:21,371
- [woman] Jho!
- Hi! Bye!

602
00:26:21,454 --> 00:26:23,290
[Jhoanna] It's great that

603
00:26:23,373 --> 00:26:24,624
we're getting
recognized individually as well.

604
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:26,793
Like, "Hi, BINI Jhoanna!"

605
00:26:26,876 --> 00:26:30,463
People call us by our names.

606
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:33,300
[woman] Ready?

607
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:35,468
Three, two, one!

608
00:26:35,552 --> 00:26:36,511
Hey!

609
00:26:36,594 --> 00:26:38,471
- Hey!
- Hey!

610
00:26:38,555 --> 00:26:41,850
[stirring music playing]

611
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:43,268
Whoo!

612
00:26:44,102 --> 00:26:44,978
Aah!

613
00:26:45,061 --> 00:26:46,980
[laughs]

614
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,700
Come on!

615
00:26:58,783 --> 00:26:59,659
I'll give you a tour.

616
00:26:59,743 --> 00:27:03,997
[stirring music continues]

617
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:06,750
For the last <i>ASAP</i> show,
which was in Vegas,

618
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:08,126
we had such a small part.

619
00:27:08,209 --> 00:27:10,128
But we were grateful to just be there

620
00:27:10,211 --> 00:27:13,298
considering we weren't that popular yet.

621
00:27:14,549 --> 00:27:17,594
So for <i>ASAP</i> California, we were surprised.

622
00:27:17,677 --> 00:27:19,137
We were in the spotlight.

623
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,306
- [Jolina] Sisters!
- [BINI cheer]

624
00:27:21,389 --> 00:27:23,183
- Let's dance!
- [laughs]

625
00:27:23,266 --> 00:27:29,105
[upbeat music playing]

626
00:27:29,189 --> 00:27:32,025
[Mikha] This was different from 2022.

627
00:27:32,108 --> 00:27:35,612
We weren't that popular yet.
There were less cheers.

628
00:27:35,695 --> 00:27:40,200
[Stacey] What if
we only had fans in the Philippines?

629
00:27:40,283 --> 00:27:45,163
[upbeat music continues]

630
00:27:45,246 --> 00:27:49,084
[Colet] Our goal is to entertain

631
00:27:49,167 --> 00:27:53,088
all the Filipinos who were going to watch.

632
00:27:53,171 --> 00:27:54,964
We gave our best,

633
00:27:55,048 --> 00:27:56,883
from rehearsals to the actual performance.

634
00:27:56,966 --> 00:27:59,677
[upbeat music continues]

635
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:06,810
- Are there people?
- No.

636
00:28:07,602 --> 00:28:09,854
- Proceed to the elevator.
- Okay.

637
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:11,815
You didn't eat?

638
00:28:11,898 --> 00:28:13,400
I did.

639
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:14,567
I'm sleepy.

640
00:28:17,070 --> 00:28:18,405
Where's Stacey?

641
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:22,117
[Maloi] We had such a busy schedule.

642
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:26,496
We were maximizing each day we were there.

643
00:28:26,579 --> 00:28:28,331
We weren't just there for <i>ASAP.</i>

644
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:33,086
We had a lot of content
to shoot and interviews to do.

645
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:38,216
We were tired. Our energy was down.

646
00:28:38,299 --> 00:28:43,805
We just wanted to rest
when we got to the hotel.

647
00:28:49,352 --> 00:28:53,940
[harmonizing]

648
00:29:03,992 --> 00:29:04,909
[Jhoanna] What are you looking at?

649
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:06,870
Hmm?

650
00:29:06,953 --> 00:29:07,954
Can I help you?

651
00:29:08,705 --> 00:29:11,124
[Mickey] There are
times you feel helpless.

652
00:29:11,207 --> 00:29:14,085
We don't always know
how to deal with everything.

653
00:29:14,169 --> 00:29:17,505
They're not little girls anymore

654
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:20,592
that cry for no reason.

655
00:29:20,675 --> 00:29:23,261
No. I think right now...

656
00:29:23,344 --> 00:29:26,598
I appreciate that they're slowly finding

657
00:29:26,681 --> 00:29:27,557
their voice as artists.

658
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:31,269
[upbeat music playing]

659
00:29:31,352 --> 00:29:36,274
[Corey] They're a phenomenal new
generation Filipino girl group.

660
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:38,276
They've made noise all over.

661
00:29:38,359 --> 00:29:41,613
[upbeat music continues]

662
00:29:41,696 --> 00:29:44,032
You can feel that they're bound by love.

663
00:29:44,115 --> 00:29:46,743
It's a genuine sisterhood,

664
00:29:46,826 --> 00:29:48,578
it's genuine camaraderie

665
00:29:48,661 --> 00:29:51,498
that really speaks to the audience.

666
00:29:51,581 --> 00:29:54,793
We're all here back in
California to celebrate...

667
00:29:54,876 --> 00:29:56,503
[Corey] When we brought ASAP to the US,

668
00:29:56,586 --> 00:29:59,047
the Blooms were there.

669
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:01,257
What they went through in 2024,

670
00:30:01,341 --> 00:30:04,969
it was growth that I feel like

671
00:30:05,053 --> 00:30:08,807
was very challenging and scary.

672
00:30:08,890 --> 00:30:11,267
But it was part of
the process of who they are now.

673
00:30:11,351 --> 00:30:13,812
They won't stop until they reach

674
00:30:13,895 --> 00:30:16,147
their global aspirations.

675
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:17,232
[audience cheering]

676
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:21,986
[cheering continues]

677
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:26,449
[upbeat music continues]

678
00:30:26,533 --> 00:30:28,243
[Corey] I call it good noise.

679
00:30:28,326 --> 00:30:31,913
That good noise
spreads around like wildfire.

680
00:30:31,996 --> 00:30:33,623
Can I do it like this?

681
00:30:34,541 --> 00:30:35,583
[chuckles]

682
00:30:35,667 --> 00:30:42,298
- [audience cheering]
- [upbeat music continues]

683
00:30:44,926 --> 00:30:46,052
[cheering continues]

684
00:30:46,135 --> 00:30:47,470
[Robi] <i>California, get ready for</i>

685
00:30:47,554 --> 00:30:49,389
<i>a mini concert like no other</i>

686
00:30:49,472 --> 00:30:52,892
<i>from the nation's girl group, BINI!</i>

687
00:30:52,976 --> 00:30:59,941
["Cherry On Top" by BINI playing]

688
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:16,249
[Aiah] It's like we had a mini concert.

689
00:31:16,332 --> 00:31:17,876
We performed and had spiels.

690
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:20,461
Before, we would
just leave after performing.

691
00:31:20,545 --> 00:31:22,171
But we've leveled up on <i>ASAP.</i>

692
00:31:22,255 --> 00:31:24,924
["Cherry On Top" continues]

693
00:31:25,008 --> 00:31:27,635
[cheering, whooping]

694
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:30,096
[Sheena] There were so many Blooms there.

695
00:31:30,179 --> 00:31:32,974
They showed us that we're loved

696
00:31:33,057 --> 00:31:34,809
and that we have fans in California.

697
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:36,519
The Blooms around the world

698
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:39,939
have been the ambassadors of BINI.

699
00:31:40,023 --> 00:31:43,276
And that attracts the attention

700
00:31:43,359 --> 00:31:45,445
of the international audience.

701
00:31:45,528 --> 00:31:48,573
I'm very proud. I'm very grateful.

702
00:31:48,656 --> 00:31:50,366
It's not an overnight success.

703
00:31:50,450 --> 00:31:53,119
It's not just talent,
of course, excellent talent,

704
00:31:53,202 --> 00:31:54,787
but it's their story.

705
00:31:54,871 --> 00:31:56,539
<i>- Wow!</i>
- [Martin] <i>There you go.</i>

706
00:31:56,623 --> 00:31:57,665
<i>Surprise, BINI.</i>

707
00:31:57,749 --> 00:32:01,836
<i>We'd like to present this recognition</i>

708
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:06,341
<i>of the record industry's
Certified Gold Album Award</i>

709
00:32:06,424 --> 00:32:10,970
<i>for the albums Feel Good and Talaarawan.</i>

710
00:32:11,054 --> 00:32:12,430
<i>Whoo!</i>

711
00:32:12,513 --> 00:32:15,767
[Jhoanna] We made it to the big leagues.

712
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:19,687
Then we saw
Director Lauren tearing up on the side.

713
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,773
- [cheering, whopping]
- [clapping]

714
00:32:21,856 --> 00:32:23,399
What a surprise.

715
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:24,692
You deserve it.

716
00:32:28,112 --> 00:32:32,033
[Maloi] It was
touching to see how proud he was

717
00:32:32,116 --> 00:32:33,409
of what we had achieved.

718
00:32:33,493 --> 00:32:38,748
It was a proud moment to
be awarded in front of our fans.

719
00:32:38,831 --> 00:32:40,416
We were so happy.

720
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:41,960
Yeah, it was very memorable.

721
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:45,672
Finally, after years of hard work,

722
00:32:45,755 --> 00:32:49,008
we are now being seen and heard.

723
00:32:49,092 --> 00:32:53,137
I am over the moon
that BINI is finally being recognized.

724
00:32:53,221 --> 00:32:56,307
Hopefully, we make it globally as well.

725
00:32:56,391 --> 00:33:02,480
[gentle music playing]

726
00:33:02,563 --> 00:33:05,108
[shouts, laughs]

727
00:33:05,191 --> 00:33:08,444
[laughing, shouting]

728
00:33:08,528 --> 00:33:10,863
- [exclaims]
- Whoa!

729
00:33:10,947 --> 00:33:11,781
Whoo!

730
00:33:20,415 --> 00:33:22,208
BINI Jhoanna, hi!

731
00:33:22,291 --> 00:33:25,753
We had a music camp two years ago.

732
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:26,838
We invited the BINI girls,

733
00:33:26,921 --> 00:33:28,339
but only two of them were available.

734
00:33:28,423 --> 00:33:29,882
- Maloi and Colet.
- Mm-hmm.

735
00:33:29,966 --> 00:33:32,677
[humming]

736
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:36,681
[singing] <i>♪ In the idea... ♪</i>

737
00:33:36,764 --> 00:33:39,767
They were interviewed
by songwriters and producers

738
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:40,727
from the US.

739
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:43,146
And then, the girls shared their ideas.

740
00:33:43,229 --> 00:33:45,773
That's how <i>Cherry On Top</i> was made

741
00:33:45,857 --> 00:33:48,067
- in the music camp. Yeah.
- That was in Davao.

742
00:33:48,151 --> 00:33:51,195
[mellow music playing]

743
00:33:51,279 --> 00:33:54,866
So, that started
our push for globalization.

744
00:33:59,162 --> 00:34:00,538
[Sheena] The girls
and I always feel anxious

745
00:34:00,621 --> 00:34:03,124
every time we release a song.

746
00:34:03,207 --> 00:34:06,669
We're worried if people
will accept and love the song.

747
00:34:06,753 --> 00:34:08,337
[mellow music continues]

748
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:11,507
[indistinct chatter]

749
00:34:11,591 --> 00:34:14,927
Some Filipinos think,
including the old me,

750
00:34:15,011 --> 00:34:18,514
that a full-English song
can't be considered OPM,

751
00:34:18,598 --> 00:34:19,807
which is not the case.

752
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:23,936
- [mellow music continues]
- [indistinct chatter]

753
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:26,856
Some people comment,
"Why is BINI's song in English?

754
00:34:26,939 --> 00:34:29,192
They're transitioning too fast.

755
00:34:29,275 --> 00:34:31,486
Cherries don't even grow in our country."

756
00:34:31,569 --> 00:34:32,653
We've encountered comments like that.

757
00:34:35,198 --> 00:34:36,908
[Mikha] When we went to the Wish Bus,

758
00:34:36,991 --> 00:34:39,077
we noticed that there
were only four Blooms.

759
00:34:39,160 --> 00:34:40,495
I didn't say anything

760
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:41,954
because I didn't want
to bring the energy down.

761
00:34:43,623 --> 00:34:45,083
Mic. Mic check. One, two.

762
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:48,127
[Mikha] One of
the Wishbus staff members said,

763
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,671
"Hi, a lot of fans are
waiting for you, guys."

764
00:34:50,755 --> 00:34:51,756
I was surprised because
I thought there were only four.

765
00:34:51,839 --> 00:34:58,805
- ["Cherry On Top" playing]
- [cheering]

766
00:35:01,307 --> 00:35:04,936
There were more people than when we did
our first Wish Bus performance

767
00:35:05,019 --> 00:35:06,562
in the Philippines, which was amazing.

768
00:35:06,646 --> 00:35:10,775
["Cherry On Top" continues]

769
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:13,069
We see a significant
rise in the number of streams.

770
00:35:13,152 --> 00:35:16,364
I think we're able to
target more Blooms overseas.

771
00:35:16,447 --> 00:35:19,200
<i>Cherry On Top</i> received
a million streams in less than 24 hours.

772
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:21,661
The girls and I were really amazed.

773
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:24,372
People are now looking
forward to our new releases.

774
00:35:24,455 --> 00:35:28,751
["Cherry On Top" continues]

775
00:35:32,004 --> 00:35:33,214
Good morning.

776
00:35:36,050 --> 00:35:36,884
Good morning.

777
00:35:45,852 --> 00:35:51,858
[indistinct chatter]

778
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:52,942
It's moving.

779
00:35:53,025 --> 00:35:54,360
- So, it's easier?
- Yeah.

780
00:35:54,443 --> 00:35:56,571
I will teach this second eight.

781
00:35:56,654 --> 00:35:58,030
Who will she be paired with?

782
00:35:58,114 --> 00:36:00,324
So, we can break down the voice.

783
00:36:00,408 --> 00:36:01,742
So, who will it be?

784
00:36:01,826 --> 00:36:03,494
You can pair me with Maloi.

785
00:36:03,578 --> 00:36:04,745
I'll do the dancing.

786
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:06,038
Alright.

787
00:36:06,122 --> 00:36:07,748
You will explain it, and I will dance.

788
00:36:07,832 --> 00:36:10,126
- In English.
- Yeah.

789
00:36:10,209 --> 00:36:16,382
["Cherry On Top" by BINI playing]

790
00:36:16,465 --> 00:36:18,926
Historically, when we created BINI,

791
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:22,263
we weren't sure yet
what their music would be like.

792
00:36:22,346 --> 00:36:27,059
The first two EPs,
especially the first EP...

793
00:36:27,143 --> 00:36:30,521
["Born To Win" by BINI playing]

794
00:36:30,605 --> 00:36:33,608
That album is
a sampler of different sounds

795
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:34,650
that BINI can make.

796
00:36:36,527 --> 00:36:37,445
The first year was okay.

797
00:36:37,528 --> 00:36:39,280
There were some who liked them.

798
00:36:39,363 --> 00:36:40,698
The second one which is...

799
00:36:40,781 --> 00:36:43,659
["I Feel Good" by BINI playing]

800
00:36:43,743 --> 00:36:46,662
We were slightly trying Asian pop songs.

801
00:36:47,413 --> 00:36:48,581
Come closer.

802
00:36:48,664 --> 00:36:54,503
[indistinct chatter]

803
00:36:54,587 --> 00:36:56,589
You two were late, Mikha.

804
00:36:57,632 --> 00:36:58,966
I can't believe we're here.

805
00:36:59,050 --> 00:37:01,135
- This is Steezy.
- [chuckles]

806
00:37:01,219 --> 00:37:02,678
I could only watch this before.

807
00:37:02,762 --> 00:37:04,013
Oh my god.

808
00:37:04,096 --> 00:37:05,306
Thank you, Lord.

809
00:37:05,389 --> 00:37:06,933
Was it good?

810
00:37:07,642 --> 00:37:09,602
This one's better. Next take.

811
00:37:09,685 --> 00:37:12,188
For the third one, we wanted

812
00:37:12,271 --> 00:37:14,899
to revolutionize OPM

813
00:37:14,982 --> 00:37:16,359
through BINI.

814
00:37:16,442 --> 00:37:17,526
That's why we created...

815
00:37:17,610 --> 00:37:20,071
["Pantropiko" by BINI playing]

816
00:37:20,154 --> 00:37:21,781
[Aiah] <i>Pantropiko</i> is so important

817
00:37:21,864 --> 00:37:24,992
because without <i>Pantropiko,</i>
where would BINI be?

818
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:26,035
Just kidding!

819
00:37:26,118 --> 00:37:28,829
You see, we didn't really expect it.

820
00:37:28,913 --> 00:37:30,706
<i>Pantropiko</i> is what...

821
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:33,376
placed us on the map.

822
00:37:33,459 --> 00:37:38,339
[music playing over speakers]

823
00:37:38,422 --> 00:37:39,257
You got it.

824
00:37:40,007 --> 00:37:41,133
I think that's it.

825
00:37:41,217 --> 00:37:42,426
I'm fine.

826
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:45,471
That's when Sheena's
iconic dance chorus happened.

827
00:37:45,554 --> 00:37:48,015
Everything started there for me.

828
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:50,226
["Cherry On Top" playing over speakers]

829
00:37:50,309 --> 00:37:53,896
[cheering]

830
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:58,442
My partner and
I watched you grow on Instagram.

831
00:37:58,526 --> 00:38:00,945
Not just because of the following but...

832
00:38:01,028 --> 00:38:03,614
everything you're producing,
like your vocals and new music.

833
00:38:03,698 --> 00:38:06,200
All of my friends went to KCON.

834
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:09,578
- Wow!
- They were gushing about you.

835
00:38:09,662 --> 00:38:10,830
And I was like...

836
00:38:10,913 --> 00:38:12,164
[laughing]

837
00:38:12,248 --> 00:38:14,292
[indistinct chatter]

838
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:15,543
Come here.

839
00:38:18,129 --> 00:38:24,885
- [camera shutter clicking]
- [upbeat music playing]

840
00:38:25,886 --> 00:38:29,181
BINI's sound is
the sound of the current generation.

841
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:32,435
We've been observing the trends

842
00:38:32,518 --> 00:38:34,937
so we can catch up to that style of music,

843
00:38:35,021 --> 00:38:38,274
which will be
the perfect sound for BINI to carry.

844
00:38:39,942 --> 00:38:43,362
That will put them on
the global map as BINI.

845
00:38:43,446 --> 00:38:45,489
Based on our experience
in the music industry...

846
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:50,411
["Pantropiko" by BINI playing]

847
00:38:50,494 --> 00:38:56,584
["Cherry On Top" by BINI playing]

848
00:38:56,667 --> 00:39:00,254
We know that once an artist or group

849
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:03,215
from another country
dances to a certain song,

850
00:39:03,299 --> 00:39:08,387
the owner of that song
is ready to go international.

851
00:39:09,597 --> 00:39:16,020
[mellow music playing]

852
00:39:16,103 --> 00:39:17,813
When Billboard Philippines called

853
00:39:17,897 --> 00:39:20,358
to inform us that BINI and
SB19 would receive awards

854
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:21,484
in Seoul, South Korea,

855
00:39:21,567 --> 00:39:24,070
we realized that was the start of...

856
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:26,447
The Philippine music wave.

857
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:28,908
...the invasion of Asian music.

858
00:39:28,991 --> 00:39:29,950
So, I think that's the first step.

859
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:33,204
They also won awards
from MTV Europe Music Awards

860
00:39:33,287 --> 00:39:36,207
and BreakTudo Awards in Brazil.

861
00:39:36,290 --> 00:39:38,626
They were recognized
with the help of the Blooms.

862
00:39:38,709 --> 00:39:41,545
We're done, guys. [claps]

863
00:39:41,629 --> 00:39:44,840
It was really fun.
I learned a lot, I swear.

864
00:39:46,425 --> 00:39:48,677
- Oh!
- Yeah!

865
00:39:48,761 --> 00:39:50,763
We have Filipinos right here.

866
00:39:50,846 --> 00:39:52,348
- Certified.
- Certified. [laughs]

867
00:39:52,431 --> 00:39:53,307
Maloi-certified.

868
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:55,059
[Gwen] BINI has been so busy that

869
00:39:55,142 --> 00:39:56,811
sometimes,
we only find out about our awards

870
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:58,687
in the middle of our events.

871
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:00,815
It's always a surprise for us.

872
00:40:00,898 --> 00:40:04,819
But of course, we're really grateful.

873
00:40:04,902 --> 00:40:09,782
It's a clear manifestation
that our hard work pays off.

874
00:40:09,865 --> 00:40:11,283
We also see on social media

875
00:40:11,367 --> 00:40:14,120
how busy the Blooms are
when there's voting involved.

876
00:40:14,203 --> 00:40:16,455
Sometimes, we feel guilty because we don't
get to interact with them

877
00:40:16,539 --> 00:40:19,166
that much due to our busy schedule.

878
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:21,293
But their support is never-ending

879
00:40:21,377 --> 00:40:23,212
even though they don't see us often.

880
00:40:23,295 --> 00:40:26,340
[indistinct chatter]

881
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:28,384
[Aiah] Every time we receive awards,

882
00:40:28,467 --> 00:40:31,220
I always look back on
our humble beginnings,

883
00:40:31,303 --> 00:40:34,932
those times when
we doubted if we would make it.

884
00:40:35,015 --> 00:40:39,520
We really didn't expect
that it would be possible.

885
00:40:42,898 --> 00:40:44,900
[singing] <i>♪ You know I'm runnin' it ♪</i>

886
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:48,654
[Aiah] We got to meet the American
producers in person for the first time.

887
00:40:48,737 --> 00:40:50,906
[singing]
<i>♪ 'Cause you know I'm runnin' it ♪</i>

888
00:40:50,990 --> 00:40:52,032
Okay, just two more.

889
00:40:52,116 --> 00:40:53,492
Really good.

890
00:40:53,576 --> 00:40:54,869
[singing] <i>♪ I heard you like confidence ♪</i>

891
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:57,913
Uh-oh! Who's the next victim?
Miss Sheena! Ah!

892
00:40:57,997 --> 00:40:59,999
Can you at least make it hard on us

893
00:41:00,082 --> 00:41:01,542
- a little bit?
- [laughs] Okay.

894
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:02,668
Yeah.

895
00:41:02,751 --> 00:41:04,336
Try not to make it so easy on us.

896
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:07,006
This is our third
time recording with them.

897
00:41:07,673 --> 00:41:12,219
We record multiple times
until we warm up our voices.

898
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:15,931
And then, they will pick the best takes.

899
00:41:16,015 --> 00:41:18,058
I'm nervous. [breathes deeply]

900
00:41:18,142 --> 00:41:19,351
Brrt!

901
00:41:19,435 --> 00:41:21,103
[Gwen] It was our first time
recording overseas. [chuckles]

902
00:41:21,187 --> 00:41:23,814
Yes, it was a very different vibe.

903
00:41:24,982 --> 00:41:27,776
[Colet] We did the recording with Greg.

904
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:29,278
He was there with me and Maloi

905
00:41:29,361 --> 00:41:31,697
when <i>Cherry On Top</i> was created in Davao.

906
00:41:31,780 --> 00:41:35,326
After <i>Cherry On Top,</i>
they gave us another song.

907
00:41:35,409 --> 00:41:36,243
It's called <i>Blink Twice.</i>

908
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:37,453
[singing] <i>♪ Symphony... ♪</i>

909
00:41:37,536 --> 00:41:39,705
- [clapping]
- [upbeat music playing]

910
00:41:45,711 --> 00:41:46,921
Is it over already?

911
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:48,881
- Not yet, sir.
- We can still watch?

912
00:41:49,673 --> 00:41:51,342
Our bosses are here.

913
00:41:52,009 --> 00:41:53,302
We were in the middle of recording

914
00:41:53,385 --> 00:41:55,596
when they suddenly arrived.

915
00:41:55,679 --> 00:41:58,182
They're going to watch us record.

916
00:41:58,265 --> 00:42:00,643
But we're all done, except for Colet.

917
00:42:00,726 --> 00:42:03,020
I feel nervous.
I thought it'd just be a video call.

918
00:42:04,563 --> 00:42:08,359
I forgot that they're in the US, too.

919
00:42:08,442 --> 00:42:10,528
[upbeat music continues]

920
00:42:10,611 --> 00:42:12,446
[vocalizing]

921
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:14,490
This is the most
nervous I've been while recording.

922
00:42:14,573 --> 00:42:21,580
[upbeat music continues]

923
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:32,508
[singing]
<i>♪ He's not even thinkin' 'bout me ♪</i>

924
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:39,723
- I'm good?
- You're great.

925
00:42:39,807 --> 00:42:40,808
Yes!

926
00:42:41,517 --> 00:42:42,434
Headphones off.

927
00:42:42,518 --> 00:42:44,311
Thank you, Lord. Hallelujah.

928
00:42:44,395 --> 00:42:46,021
- Ah!
- Damn!

929
00:42:46,105 --> 00:42:48,482
Next time make
it a little harder on us, would you?

930
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:49,567
- [chuckling]
- [clapping]

931
00:42:49,650 --> 00:42:51,068
I'm glad I made it in time to watch you.

932
00:42:51,151 --> 00:42:52,111
[laughing]

933
00:42:52,194 --> 00:42:54,113
I just have to say that you girls

934
00:42:54,196 --> 00:42:56,115
are seriously one of
the easiest vocal sessions

935
00:42:56,198 --> 00:42:58,075
- I've ever done.
- Wow! [clapping]

936
00:42:58,158 --> 00:42:59,827
And I've done some
heavy-duty vocal sessions.

937
00:42:59,910 --> 00:43:02,830
Yay! [clapping]

938
00:43:02,913 --> 00:43:05,082
[all] Hi, we are BINI,

939
00:43:05,165 --> 00:43:07,126
and you’re listening to KPOP radio.

940
00:43:07,209 --> 00:43:09,670
[all] Eyyy!

941
00:43:09,753 --> 00:43:11,672
[Carlo] <i>They have the heart for it</i>

942
00:43:11,755 --> 00:43:13,632
<i>a different kind of
passion for what they do,</i>

943
00:43:13,716 --> 00:43:17,261
<i>but there's also
that element of Filipino kindness.</i>

944
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:18,178
<i>It shines through.</i>

945
00:43:18,262 --> 00:43:20,139
<i>I think that's what makes them special.</i>

946
00:43:20,222 --> 00:43:21,724
<i>I think the success of BINI</i>

947
00:43:21,807 --> 00:43:27,313
should be based not on
the need to have a diverse representation

948
00:43:27,396 --> 00:43:30,149
but really because their talent is unique

949
00:43:30,232 --> 00:43:31,317
<i>and their talent is amazing.</i>

950
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:34,653
<i>Not because of
their ethnicity or nationality.</i>

951
00:43:34,737 --> 00:43:36,447
<i>Let them shine
because of how great they are.</i>

952
00:43:36,530 --> 00:43:38,699
<i>Let them shine because of who they are.</i>

953
00:43:38,782 --> 00:43:40,200
[upbeat music playing]

954
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:41,869
- Miss Agnez.
- [Agnez] Oh, hey!

955
00:43:43,370 --> 00:43:44,455
This is Agnez Mo.

956
00:43:44,538 --> 00:43:46,165
- [Agnez] Hey!
- Hi!

957
00:43:46,248 --> 00:43:48,000
How are you doing? Hey, I'm Agnez.

958
00:43:48,083 --> 00:43:50,085
[Mikha] <i>We were all intimidated at first</i>

959
00:43:50,169 --> 00:43:53,505
<i>because she’s
a very big artist in Indonesia</i>

960
00:43:53,589 --> 00:43:54,715
<i>and everywhere else.</i>

961
00:43:54,798 --> 00:43:58,093
It was nice to talk to
her because she was very humble,

962
00:43:58,177 --> 00:43:59,178
down to earth.

963
00:43:59,261 --> 00:44:00,679
She was giving us advice.

964
00:44:00,763 --> 00:44:02,681
[Gwen] Actually, I saw her outside,

965
00:44:02,765 --> 00:44:03,724
she was sitting at that time.

966
00:44:03,807 --> 00:44:06,685
Good thing I was
smiling when I went out. [laughs]

967
00:44:06,769 --> 00:44:10,230
[Agnez] It’s not even
about being the most talented,

968
00:44:10,314 --> 00:44:12,358
but I think it’s who’s the better student.

969
00:44:12,441 --> 00:44:15,736
That means listening to,
you know, your team,

970
00:44:15,819 --> 00:44:18,197
but also at the same time, um...

971
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:19,657
you know, stand your ground.

972
00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:22,701
[Jhoanna] She was
very sisterly when we met her.

973
00:44:22,785 --> 00:44:24,953
[Colet] She’s been in
the industry for such a long time,

974
00:44:25,037 --> 00:44:29,667
so she gave us advice
on how to last in this business

975
00:44:29,750 --> 00:44:32,670
and how to keep
the passion for performing.

976
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:35,464
[Agnez] This is
definitely the most important.

977
00:44:35,547 --> 00:44:37,466
Get rid of toxic people.

978
00:44:37,549 --> 00:44:38,676
- Whoa.
- Yes!

979
00:44:38,759 --> 00:44:40,135
[Stacey] <i>She said to
always have a good attitude.</i>

980
00:44:40,219 --> 00:44:43,806
She taught us a lot
about how to handle bashers,

981
00:44:43,889 --> 00:44:46,684
those people who won’t leave us alone.

982
00:44:46,767 --> 00:44:48,060
[Maloi] <i>Learn to say no.</i>

983
00:44:48,143 --> 00:44:51,772
<i>You shouldn't say yes to everything.</i>

984
00:44:51,855 --> 00:44:53,649
You should have dignity.

985
00:44:53,732 --> 00:44:55,526
Stand firm in your beliefs.

986
00:44:55,609 --> 00:44:57,903
If you don't like something,
then you don't like it.

987
00:44:57,986 --> 00:44:59,238
Apart from her music,

988
00:44:59,321 --> 00:45:00,906
her personality has also played a big role

989
00:45:00,989 --> 00:45:02,157
to sustain such a long career.

990
00:45:02,241 --> 00:45:04,243
You should make
mistakes to learn from them

991
00:45:04,326 --> 00:45:06,870
and be better as an artist.

992
00:45:06,954 --> 00:45:09,289
[photographer] One, two, three...

993
00:45:10,457 --> 00:45:13,377
[Gwen] <i>We thank her for sharing
her nuggets of wisdom,</i>

994
00:45:13,460 --> 00:45:17,172
especially when it comes
to reaching global audiences.

995
00:45:17,256 --> 00:45:18,674
[thunder rolling]

996
00:45:18,757 --> 00:45:20,384
As if nothing happened, guys.

997
00:45:20,467 --> 00:45:21,677
- [chuckles]
- We're all packing.

998
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:23,971
[mellow music playing]

999
00:45:24,054 --> 00:45:25,431
Is Care Bear a priority?

1000
00:45:26,473 --> 00:45:28,559
Oh, you're trying to fit everything in.

1001
00:45:28,642 --> 00:45:32,187
- [marker scribbling]
- [overlapping chatter]

1002
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:35,941
Girls, our checkout time is 11 AM.

1003
00:45:36,024 --> 00:45:37,776
Could you come picks us up from the lobby?

1004
00:45:37,860 --> 00:45:38,777
[chuckles]

1005
00:45:38,861 --> 00:45:41,238
Oh, okay.

1006
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:42,406
[Gwen] I don't have much stuff to pack.

1007
00:45:42,489 --> 00:45:43,699
Well, that's good.

1008
00:45:43,782 --> 00:45:45,492
I didn’t overpack. I’m proud of that.

1009
00:45:45,576 --> 00:45:46,827
Bye, everyone.

1010
00:45:46,910 --> 00:45:48,787
- Bye, good night.
- Rest well.

1011
00:45:49,621 --> 00:45:52,082
- [camera shutter clicking]
- [wind howling]

1012
00:45:52,166 --> 00:45:53,250
[car revving]

1013
00:45:53,333 --> 00:45:55,169
- [airplane engine droning]
- [water rushing]

1014
00:45:56,003 --> 00:45:57,254
[airplane engine humming]

1015
00:45:57,337 --> 00:45:58,297
[camera shutter clicks]

1016
00:45:58,380 --> 00:46:02,176
[indistinct flight announcement]
over p.a.]

1017
00:46:02,259 --> 00:46:09,266
[mellow music continues]

1018
00:46:12,394 --> 00:46:18,442
[ambient city noise]

1019
00:46:18,525 --> 00:46:19,359
Okay.

1020
00:46:22,738 --> 00:46:24,615
[Aiah] <i>Actually,
we didn’t expect to go to Canada.</i>

1021
00:46:24,698 --> 00:46:29,244
I honestly thought
we would have a tour in the US.

1022
00:46:29,328 --> 00:46:30,704
But it’s nice.

1023
00:46:30,787 --> 00:46:33,332
<i>We got to go to four different cities.</i>

1024
00:46:33,415 --> 00:46:35,959
[guide] If you want to film
the bridge here, it’s really nice.

1025
00:46:36,043 --> 00:46:37,961
[Jhoanna] <i>The difficult
part of our Canada tour</i>

1026
00:46:38,045 --> 00:46:39,671
<i>was that it was just basically us.</i>

1027
00:46:39,755 --> 00:46:41,381
<i>We didn’t have a big team,</i>

1028
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:43,926
unlike our NFT concert
where everyone was there.

1029
00:46:44,009 --> 00:46:46,803
[thrilling music playing]

1030
00:46:46,887 --> 00:46:48,931
- Good morning!
- Good morning!

1031
00:46:50,307 --> 00:46:52,559
It's our concert day today.

1032
00:46:52,643 --> 00:46:54,853
- Finally, some Filipino food!
- Thank You, Lord!

1033
00:46:54,937 --> 00:46:57,189
[Jhoanna] For our Canada stops,
we only had Coach Mickey...

1034
00:46:58,565 --> 00:47:00,859
That's the problem with tours abroad.

1035
00:47:00,943 --> 00:47:03,028
And you only have
the day itself for everything.

1036
00:47:03,111 --> 00:47:05,072
Sometimes, things get lost in translation.

1037
00:47:05,155 --> 00:47:07,407
[Jhoanna] <i>...Mommy Jho, and Miss Ice.</i>

1038
00:47:07,491 --> 00:47:09,201
<i>So we had a hard time,</i>

1039
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:10,953
especially backstage during the concert.

1040
00:47:11,036 --> 00:47:13,205
There really wasn’t anyone helping us.

1041
00:47:13,288 --> 00:47:14,373
[light music playing]

1042
00:47:14,456 --> 00:47:15,791
- Toronto!
- Toronto!

1043
00:47:15,874 --> 00:47:17,167
Hi, Toronto!

1044
00:47:17,251 --> 00:47:19,169
- Mic check.
- Guys, I think--

1045
00:47:19,253 --> 00:47:21,255
[Stacey] We rehearsed the whole day.

1046
00:47:21,338 --> 00:47:23,215
Endless rehearsals.

1047
00:47:23,298 --> 00:47:26,760
We always have to train
ourselves on different stages.

1048
00:47:26,843 --> 00:47:28,679
And that one was new for us.

1049
00:47:28,762 --> 00:47:33,350
[stirring music playing]

1050
00:47:33,433 --> 00:47:35,269
- Oh my!
- [chuckles]

1051
00:47:35,352 --> 00:47:36,436
[Jhoanna] No backup
dancers, so we go straight...

1052
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:39,231
Who didn't eat? Why didn't you eat?

1053
00:47:39,314 --> 00:47:41,483
Girls, help each other backstage, okay?

1054
00:47:41,567 --> 00:47:42,442
One, two...

1055
00:47:42,526 --> 00:47:44,027
[all] BINI!

1056
00:47:44,111 --> 00:47:45,362
- Alright. Cool, cool.
- Wow.

1057
00:47:45,445 --> 00:47:47,489
- Wow, that was on three.
- That was on three.

1058
00:47:47,573 --> 00:47:49,491
[thrilling music playing]

1059
00:47:49,575 --> 00:47:50,659
[Coach Mickey]
<i>Talent is important in anything</i>

1060
00:47:50,742 --> 00:47:51,952
that you’re doing.

1061
00:47:52,035 --> 00:47:53,120
<i>But as it shows...</i>

1062
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:55,122
Let's go!

1063
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:57,332
...skill will always outdo talent.

1064
00:47:57,416 --> 00:47:58,834
<i>Because if you’re talented,</i>

1065
00:47:58,917 --> 00:47:59,835
<i>sometimes you get lazy.</i>

1066
00:47:59,918 --> 00:48:00,836
Complacent.

1067
00:48:00,919 --> 00:48:03,964
<i>But if you’re skilled,
you know you worked hard for it,</i>

1068
00:48:04,047 --> 00:48:05,007
<i>and you keep on learning.</i>

1069
00:48:05,090 --> 00:48:07,426
What we did with
BINI was talent and skill.

1070
00:48:07,509 --> 00:48:08,677
[cheering, applause]

1071
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:14,933
[thrilling music continues]

1072
00:48:17,603 --> 00:48:20,022
[camera shutter clicking]

1073
00:48:20,731 --> 00:48:22,774
[whooping]

1074
00:48:22,858 --> 00:48:23,859
- Hi, BINI!
- Hi, BINI!

1075
00:48:23,942 --> 00:48:28,155
[Mikha] <i>Wow, we were able
to actually fill that many people.</i>

1076
00:48:28,238 --> 00:48:29,990
<i>Like that amount of people,</i>

1077
00:48:30,073 --> 00:48:31,074
in a different country.

1078
00:48:34,369 --> 00:48:35,245
- Whoo!
- Yeah!

1079
00:48:35,329 --> 00:48:36,747
[fan] <i>Aiah!</i>

1080
00:48:36,830 --> 00:48:38,081
[crowd screaming]

1081
00:48:38,165 --> 00:48:40,167
[Aiah] <i>That was a "wow" moment for us.</i>

1082
00:48:40,250 --> 00:48:43,211
The fact that we sold out all four cities.

1083
00:48:43,295 --> 00:48:48,967
[film rolling, clicking]

1084
00:48:50,844 --> 00:48:52,929
[vocalizing]

1085
00:48:53,013 --> 00:48:54,765
[Maloi] <i>Those are different cities.</i>

1086
00:48:54,848 --> 00:48:57,684
They really showed us warmth and love.

1087
00:48:57,768 --> 00:49:00,479
<i>We still have a lot to learn</i>

1088
00:49:00,562 --> 00:49:03,815
<i>to truly reach the level of excellence</i>

1089
00:49:03,899 --> 00:49:05,776
required in the international scene.

1090
00:49:05,859 --> 00:49:10,322
But with the help of our foundation,
the Filipino fans,

1091
00:49:10,405 --> 00:49:14,034
if they keep believing in our talents,

1092
00:49:14,117 --> 00:49:17,537
if they continue giving us
the courage to push ahead,

1093
00:49:17,621 --> 00:49:20,624
and if they keep
showing us their all-out support,

1094
00:49:20,707 --> 00:49:22,292
then we can definitely do it.

1095
00:49:22,376 --> 00:49:29,383
["Diyan Ka Lang" playing]

1096
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:35,055
[coach Mickey]
<i>In Canada, we were able to see</i>

1097
00:49:35,138 --> 00:49:36,431
<i>that it was the kids who attended.</i>

1098
00:49:36,515 --> 00:49:38,266
Music is a language,

1099
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:42,062
and it will help
you get closer to your culture,

1100
00:49:42,145 --> 00:49:43,647
or in this case, to other cultures.

1101
00:49:44,731 --> 00:49:46,692
<i>To show them the culture,</i>

1102
00:49:46,775 --> 00:49:48,318
<i>especially this generation’s culture,</i>

1103
00:49:48,402 --> 00:49:50,195
<i>and to tell it through songs...</i>

1104
00:49:50,278 --> 00:49:52,406
Personally,
I think it was a big stepping stone,

1105
00:49:52,489 --> 00:49:53,615
what we did here,

1106
00:49:53,699 --> 00:49:55,075
but I think we’re still very far.

1107
00:49:55,158 --> 00:49:57,869
So we were like, "If we sold out there,

1108
00:49:57,953 --> 00:50:02,499
maybe we can also sell out Araneta."

1109
00:50:02,582 --> 00:50:07,462
["Diyan Ka Lang" instrumental playing]

1110
00:50:07,546 --> 00:50:09,673
We thought we'd only
have a few concerts this year,

1111
00:50:09,756 --> 00:50:10,799
the NFT concert.

1112
00:50:10,882 --> 00:50:12,384
Then suddenly there’s an announcement

1113
00:50:12,467 --> 00:50:14,761
that we’ll have
the Grand BINIverse at Araneta.

1114
00:50:16,930 --> 00:50:19,725
<i>Two days weren’t enough,
we needed a third day.</i>

1115
00:50:19,808 --> 00:50:21,977
So even though
we were tired, we pushed through

1116
00:50:22,060 --> 00:50:24,771
because we felt bad for
the Blooms who couldn’t come.

1117
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:28,984
We really wanted many
Blooms to watch the Grand BINIverse.

1118
00:50:29,067 --> 00:50:30,026
It really was grand.

1119
00:50:30,110 --> 00:50:33,405
["Diyan Ka Lang" playing]

1120
00:50:33,488 --> 00:50:34,990
[music fading]

1121
00:50:35,073 --> 00:50:37,075
<i>We'll be joined by the members of BINI.</i>

1122
00:50:37,159 --> 00:50:39,453
<i>We have Jhoanna, we have Maloi,</i>

1123
00:50:39,536 --> 00:50:40,996
<i>we have Mikha, and we have Colet.</i>

1124
00:50:41,079 --> 00:50:43,081
<i>Of course, girls,
first of all, congratulations...</i>

1125
00:50:43,165 --> 00:50:47,502
- [static noise]
- [camera shutters clicking]

1126
00:50:47,586 --> 00:50:49,880
[music fades]

1127
00:50:49,963 --> 00:50:51,757
[Colet] <i>At that moment,
I wasn't feeling okay anymore.</i>

1128
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:54,676
<i>The fans had given us letters,</i>

1129
00:50:54,760 --> 00:50:56,845
and the one that reached me

1130
00:50:57,471 --> 00:50:59,723
<i>said something like, um...</i>

1131
00:50:59,806 --> 00:51:00,974
<i>Uh...</i>

1132
00:51:01,057 --> 00:51:03,810
<i>"Your music saved me.</i>

1133
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:06,730
BINI is always my source...

1134
00:51:06,813 --> 00:51:13,403
- [somber music playing]
- [indistinct chattering]

1135
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:14,738
<i>...of happiness.</i>

1136
00:51:14,821 --> 00:51:19,367
<i>My anxiety goes away
because you girls always make me laugh.</i>

1137
00:51:19,451 --> 00:51:21,953
<i>You're all so authentic.</i>

1138
00:51:22,037 --> 00:51:24,748
And then it hit me.

1139
00:51:25,832 --> 00:51:27,501
I’m helping other people,

1140
00:51:27,584 --> 00:51:30,003
but no one is helping me figure out

1141
00:51:30,086 --> 00:51:31,797
how-- how to make...

1142
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:33,298
how to make my anxiety go away,

1143
00:51:33,381 --> 00:51:36,593
how deal with this feeling.

1144
00:51:42,849 --> 00:51:43,934
<i>Because the other girls</i>

1145
00:51:44,017 --> 00:51:46,645
have someone waiting
for them when they get home.

1146
00:51:46,728 --> 00:51:49,272
Whether it's family or someone else.

1147
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:51,858
But who doesn't have anyone? Me.

1148
00:51:51,942 --> 00:51:54,444
I'm always alone.

1149
00:51:54,528 --> 00:51:56,571
So, I'd rather be outside,

1150
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:58,532
I'd rather keep training
even though it's exhausting.

1151
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:00,450
At least then, I'm not alone.

1152
00:52:01,868 --> 00:52:03,829
So, during that time at the screening...

1153
00:52:03,912 --> 00:52:05,288
[crowd cheering]

1154
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:07,082
[emcee] <i>BINI Colet!</i>

1155
00:52:08,875 --> 00:52:11,253
<i>BINI Mikha!</i>

1156
00:52:11,336 --> 00:52:12,754
<i>...I couldn't look at the crowd.</i>

1157
00:52:12,838 --> 00:52:15,674
<i>I don't know why,
but whenever I see a lot of people,</i>

1158
00:52:15,757 --> 00:52:17,008
<i>I start to panic.</i>

1159
00:52:17,092 --> 00:52:20,262
All I really wanted at
that time was to sit down. [chuckles]

1160
00:52:20,929 --> 00:52:27,060
- [loud thumping]
- [gloomy music playing]

1161
00:52:27,143 --> 00:52:28,019
[Mikha] <i>She was crying so much.</i>

1162
00:52:28,103 --> 00:52:29,896
Like, she couldn’t stop herself.

1163
00:52:29,980 --> 00:52:31,690
We were surprised,

1164
00:52:31,773 --> 00:52:32,816
and then we realized
that something was wrong.

1165
00:52:32,899 --> 00:52:36,987
[tender music playing]

1166
00:52:37,070 --> 00:52:38,446
[Colet] <i>My sisters were checking on me,</i>

1167
00:52:38,530 --> 00:52:40,282
<i>but I don’t usually
share much with my family.</i>

1168
00:52:40,365 --> 00:52:45,036
They even used to say
that what happened to me

1169
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:47,163
was the same as what happened to Aiah.

1170
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:49,958
My family was really panicking.

1171
00:52:50,041 --> 00:52:52,460
My sister even said
that she'd file for leave for me.

1172
00:52:52,544 --> 00:52:53,545
She flew here to see me.

1173
00:52:53,628 --> 00:52:54,838
[film rolling]

1174
00:52:55,922 --> 00:52:57,883
<i>That month had been</i> so exhausting for us,

1175
00:52:57,966 --> 00:53:00,760
<i>so we decided to spend a rest day</i>

1176
00:53:00,844 --> 00:53:02,470
doing Bible study.

1177
00:53:02,554 --> 00:53:05,098
I remember Aiah leading it then.

1178
00:53:05,181 --> 00:53:08,310
[soft music playing]

1179
00:53:08,393 --> 00:53:09,686
[Aiah] <i>And that was when she shared</i>

1180
00:53:09,769 --> 00:53:11,605
<i>that she had an anxiety attack,</i>

1181
00:53:11,688 --> 00:53:15,775
<i>and I told her some things</i>

1182
00:53:15,859 --> 00:53:17,569
about what I went through as well.

1183
00:53:17,652 --> 00:53:20,113
What I felt, how I overcame it.

1184
00:53:20,196 --> 00:53:24,659
It happens to a lot of
people more than you think,

1185
00:53:24,743 --> 00:53:26,620
<i>but they don’t show it.</i>

1186
00:53:26,703 --> 00:53:30,040
<i>I felt sad I wasn't
aware of her struggles.</i>

1187
00:53:30,123 --> 00:53:32,918
[photographer] Family picture!

1188
00:53:33,543 --> 00:53:35,629
Okay, get closer, Staku.

1189
00:53:37,964 --> 00:53:39,090
[Colet] I took the risk and told myself,

1190
00:53:39,174 --> 00:53:40,383
"Okay, I’ll share this."

1191
00:53:40,467 --> 00:53:42,344
[Maloi] <i>She allowed us,
her fellow BINI girls,</i>

1192
00:53:42,427 --> 00:53:46,306
<i>to cross that line and embrace her fully.</i>

1193
00:53:46,389 --> 00:53:52,312
We heard stories that we don't
usually share with each other.

1194
00:53:52,395 --> 00:53:56,566
It’s nice to know
that we all came together to...

1195
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:59,444
to focus on...

1196
00:53:59,527 --> 00:54:02,030
<i>making a connection with God</i>

1197
00:54:02,113 --> 00:54:05,033
<i>and making a connection
with everyone else in the group.</i>

1198
00:54:05,116 --> 00:54:06,284
[Gwen] Especially in this era of BINI,

1199
00:54:06,368 --> 00:54:09,079
where things happen so quickly.

1200
00:54:09,162 --> 00:54:12,374
The pressure, the changes...

1201
00:54:12,457 --> 00:54:16,878
That’s why, sometimes,
negative thoughts are inevitable.

1202
00:54:16,962 --> 00:54:18,755
Aside from a support system,

1203
00:54:18,838 --> 00:54:21,341
which I think is very essential,

1204
00:54:21,424 --> 00:54:23,760
<i>it’s also important for us girls,</i>

1205
00:54:23,843 --> 00:54:25,303
<i>who are so immersed in work</i>

1206
00:54:25,387 --> 00:54:28,056
<i>and with everything happening in BINI,</i>

1207
00:54:28,139 --> 00:54:32,602
<i>that we always have
someone professional looking after us.</i>

1208
00:54:32,686 --> 00:54:34,854
<i>We’re grateful because we have One Core.</i>

1209
00:54:34,938 --> 00:54:36,690
We’ve been celebrating
Christmas together for six years.

1210
00:54:36,773 --> 00:54:38,650
- Six years together.
- Six years?

1211
00:54:38,733 --> 00:54:41,027
- Yeah.
- Six Christmases.

1212
00:54:41,111 --> 00:54:43,905
[coach Mickey] <i>Creating a group,
honestly, I believe, is very easy.</i>

1213
00:54:43,989 --> 00:54:44,948
<i>Anyone can create a group.</i>

1214
00:54:45,031 --> 00:54:47,158
<i>But to sustain a group,</i>

1215
00:54:47,242 --> 00:54:48,868
it has not just to do with talent,

1216
00:54:48,952 --> 00:54:51,079
but it also has to do with understanding

1217
00:54:51,162 --> 00:54:52,956
and working with each other

1218
00:54:53,039 --> 00:54:56,292
and loving each other during
the bad times and the good times.

1219
00:54:56,376 --> 00:54:58,336
[somber music playing]

1220
00:54:58,420 --> 00:55:00,672
[machine whirring]

1221
00:55:00,755 --> 00:55:02,132
[metal clanking]

1222
00:55:04,050 --> 00:55:08,013
[indistinct chattering]

1223
00:55:08,096 --> 00:55:10,932
Did we do that? The DJ booth?

1224
00:55:11,016 --> 00:55:12,183
I asked Jeff to handle it.

1225
00:55:12,267 --> 00:55:13,351
- Will we have one?
- Yeah.

1226
00:55:15,311 --> 00:55:16,604
Hello?

1227
00:55:18,064 --> 00:55:20,316
What's your role?

1228
00:55:21,651 --> 00:55:22,610
Where?

1229
00:55:22,694 --> 00:55:25,488
[bright music playing]

1230
00:55:25,572 --> 00:55:27,365
[coach Mickey]
<i>The Grand BINIverse was basically</i>

1231
00:55:27,449 --> 00:55:29,075
<i>a BINIverse spin-off,</i>

1232
00:55:29,159 --> 00:55:31,745
<i>which was their first
concert at the New Frontier Theater.</i>

1233
00:55:31,828 --> 00:55:34,622
And the BINIverse
was an introduction to BINI.

1234
00:55:34,706 --> 00:55:38,668
[upbeat music playing]

1235
00:55:38,752 --> 00:55:41,337
<i>For us, Grand BINIverse was a party,</i>

1236
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:44,215
<i>but the party was no
longer just about BINI.</i>

1237
00:55:44,299 --> 00:55:46,301
You were also part of it.

1238
00:55:46,384 --> 00:55:47,761
<i>So, it was more like an experience.</i>

1239
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:50,597
<i>An exchange between BINI</i>

1240
00:55:50,680 --> 00:55:52,932
<i>and the people watching them, the Blooms,</i>

1241
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:55,602
<i>and those who fell
in love with their songs.</i>

1242
00:55:55,685 --> 00:55:57,979
To us, it was a big party

1243
00:55:58,063 --> 00:56:00,565
where they were at the center,
and everyone joined in.

1244
00:56:00,648 --> 00:56:01,775
[upbeat music continues]

1245
00:56:01,858 --> 00:56:03,902
<i>From the NFT
concert and performing abroad,</i>

1246
00:56:03,985 --> 00:56:06,279
<i>to KCON, to their performances on ASAP,</i>

1247
00:56:06,362 --> 00:56:07,614
<i>to Canada...</i>

1248
00:56:07,697 --> 00:56:10,992
<i>When they returned,
you could see their growth</i>

1249
00:56:11,076 --> 00:56:12,744
and everything
that they had learned there.

1250
00:56:12,827 --> 00:56:14,412
It truly felt like a homecoming.

1251
00:56:15,121 --> 00:56:16,539
[Lauren] <i>The stress was high at that level</i>

1252
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:20,126
<i>because our NFT concert went really well.</i>

1253
00:56:22,128 --> 00:56:24,172
People will always
expect a better show after that.

1254
00:56:24,255 --> 00:56:26,049
Okay, are we complete? Don't show me.

1255
00:56:26,132 --> 00:56:27,383
- This is it!
- Okay.

1256
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:29,636
Ah! Oh my god!

1257
00:56:31,137 --> 00:56:32,764
[Stacey] <i>It felt like
everythinghappened so fast</i>

1258
00:56:32,847 --> 00:56:34,182
<i>during the Grand BINIverse.</i>

1259
00:56:34,265 --> 00:56:37,644
We only ran through
the whole show a few times.

1260
00:56:37,727 --> 00:56:39,354
I'm panicking! I'm panicking!

1261
00:56:39,437 --> 00:56:40,438
Ah!

1262
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:43,274
[Sheena] <i>BINI is in
a good place right now.</i>

1263
00:56:43,358 --> 00:56:44,275
<i>Every time I feel exhausted,</i>

1264
00:56:44,359 --> 00:56:45,944
like really tired and completely drained,

1265
00:56:46,027 --> 00:56:48,196
I just remind myself
that this is what we dreamed of.

1266
00:56:48,279 --> 00:56:49,447
What would I rather choose?

1267
00:56:49,531 --> 00:56:51,825
Being exhausted from
work or having nothing going on?

1268
00:56:51,908 --> 00:56:54,202
[laughs] There’s no
time to breathe, just kidding!

1269
00:56:54,285 --> 00:56:57,872
If I got through it before, why not now?

1270
00:56:57,956 --> 00:57:02,710
[Maloi] We were able to
focus just months or weeks prior.

1271
00:57:02,794 --> 00:57:05,463
That’s the most
challenging part: having time. It’s time.

1272
00:57:05,547 --> 00:57:12,554
[upbeat music continues]

1273
00:57:14,222 --> 00:57:16,266
[Aiah] <i>The Grand BINIverse
was lighter for us</i>

1274
00:57:16,349 --> 00:57:18,017
<i>compared to the last time.</i>

1275
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:20,520
In NFT, it was our first concert,

1276
00:57:20,603 --> 00:57:23,148
so we were still gauging,
still figuring things out.

1277
00:57:23,231 --> 00:57:24,399
Wow!

1278
00:57:24,482 --> 00:57:25,608
- Relax.
- [laughs]

1279
00:57:27,193 --> 00:57:28,319
[laughing]

1280
00:57:29,195 --> 00:57:31,072
<i>We have more rest days these days.</i>

1281
00:57:31,156 --> 00:57:34,075
<i>We started talking
about needing this and that,</i>

1282
00:57:34,159 --> 00:57:36,786
and we decided to set a hard
stop somewhere in our schedule.

1283
00:57:36,870 --> 00:57:39,289
That really helped a lot.

1284
00:57:39,372 --> 00:57:41,082
I mean, it shows.

1285
00:57:41,166 --> 00:57:43,084
So, more rest days! [chuckles]

1286
00:57:43,168 --> 00:57:50,175
[stirring music playing]

1287
00:57:51,217 --> 00:57:52,510
[Colet] <i>BINI is still healthy for us.</i>

1288
00:57:52,594 --> 00:57:54,471
<i>We really had a great
time during the Grand BINIverse.</i>

1289
00:57:54,554 --> 00:57:56,723
<i>We didn't have to worry
too much about the possibility</i>

1290
00:57:56,806 --> 00:57:58,558
of someone missing the rest of the concert

1291
00:57:58,641 --> 00:57:59,726
due to illness.

1292
00:58:03,438 --> 00:58:08,151
[Lauren] <i>Their bodies
and minds were already trained</i>

1293
00:58:08,234 --> 00:58:09,360
<i>to perform at Araneta.</i>

1294
00:58:09,444 --> 00:58:11,779
<i>So, they felt more confident</i>

1295
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:15,074
in their ability to deliver
an outstanding performance.

1296
00:58:15,158 --> 00:58:16,701
- Oh my!
- Ah!

1297
00:58:16,784 --> 00:58:17,827
Oh my god!

1298
00:58:17,911 --> 00:58:18,912
[laughter]

1299
00:58:18,995 --> 00:58:19,871
[screaming]

1300
00:58:19,954 --> 00:58:21,623
[stirring music continues]

1301
00:58:21,706 --> 00:58:22,665
Oh no!

1302
00:58:22,749 --> 00:58:24,542
I really can’t do this!

1303
00:58:24,626 --> 00:58:25,585
Oh my god!

1304
00:58:25,668 --> 00:58:28,505
That was the Grand BINIverse,
and it had to be grand.

1305
00:58:28,588 --> 00:58:30,298
I’m not really into rides, guys.

1306
00:58:30,381 --> 00:58:31,591
This feels like one.

1307
00:58:31,674 --> 00:58:33,760
And Gwen has a fear of
heights. Just our luck, really.

1308
00:58:35,178 --> 00:58:36,179
We're so high up.

1309
00:58:36,262 --> 00:58:39,390
[Mikha] Who would want to
perform on a 360-degree stage

1310
00:58:39,474 --> 00:58:43,019
with an 8-member
girl group and 26 besties?

1311
00:58:43,102 --> 00:58:44,270
Just us.

1312
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:46,773
For me, I have full
trust in Director Lauren.

1313
00:58:46,856 --> 00:58:49,984
When he says it,
I'm really confident that we can do it.

1314
00:58:50,068 --> 00:58:52,362
Ready? Lift the stage.

1315
00:58:52,445 --> 00:58:53,613
[chuckles nervously]

1316
00:58:53,696 --> 00:58:55,823
- Oh my god.
- Ooh la la, Mamma Mia!

1317
00:58:55,907 --> 00:58:57,700
[screaming]

1318
00:58:57,784 --> 00:59:00,411
[stirring music continues]

1319
00:59:00,495 --> 00:59:01,621
[coach Mickey] <i>It was a discomfort.</i>

1320
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:03,164
<i>No one was in their comfort zone.</i>

1321
00:59:03,248 --> 00:59:04,374
<i>Being in that situation,</i>

1322
00:59:04,457 --> 00:59:07,085
<i>we had to learn to
adapt and figure things out.</i>

1323
00:59:07,168 --> 00:59:08,628
<i>"How will we make it work?"</i>

1324
00:59:08,711 --> 00:59:09,837
I think that was the biggest challenge.

1325
00:59:09,921 --> 00:59:11,548
We were only able to
put everything together

1326
00:59:11,631 --> 00:59:14,342
during the technical rehearsals.

1327
00:59:14,425 --> 00:59:20,598
[stirring music continues]

1328
00:59:20,682 --> 00:59:22,141
- [bell dings]
- [music stops]

1329
00:59:23,351 --> 00:59:26,396
[Colet] <i>She was always
good at hiding her problems.</i>

1330
00:59:26,479 --> 00:59:28,606
<i>She always looked happy,
so it was really hard to tell</i>

1331
00:59:28,690 --> 00:59:31,901
if she had a problem or not.

1332
00:59:31,985 --> 00:59:35,572
[morose music playing]

1333
00:59:35,655 --> 00:59:39,325
[Jhoanna] <i>She told us in our group chat
that her dad wasn't doing well,</i>

1334
00:59:39,409 --> 00:59:41,077
<i>but we decided not to press.</i>

1335
00:59:41,160 --> 00:59:43,454
We held back from
asking, "How's your dad?"

1336
00:59:43,538 --> 00:59:45,039
because we wanted to give her space.

1337
00:59:45,123 --> 00:59:47,667
A few days before,
Maloi was still with her family

1338
00:59:47,750 --> 00:59:51,004
because we were coming
from the All Saint’s Day break.

1339
00:59:51,087 --> 00:59:53,214
[somber music playing]

1340
00:59:53,298 --> 00:59:54,966
[Maloi] Two weeks before <i>Grand BINIverse,</i>

1341
00:59:55,049 --> 00:59:58,845
Mama noticed,
“Your dad is getting thinner.”

1342
00:59:58,928 --> 01:00:01,139
I told them to have him checked.

1343
01:00:01,222 --> 01:00:03,600
Then, we found out
that he had an enlargement of the heart.

1344
01:00:05,560 --> 01:00:07,562
He was okay though,
I even saw his test results.

1345
01:00:07,645 --> 01:00:10,898
Everything was fine except for his heart,
which had an enlargement.

1346
01:00:10,982 --> 01:00:12,859
So, he really needed to be taken care of.

1347
01:00:15,778 --> 01:00:17,780
We haven't rehearsed everything yet.

1348
01:00:19,324 --> 01:00:20,742
So...

1349
01:00:20,825 --> 01:00:23,369
I feel like we'll be here until 3 AM.

1350
01:00:23,453 --> 01:00:25,330
3 AM.

1351
01:00:25,413 --> 01:00:28,416
The next day,
my sibling messaged me saying

1352
01:00:28,499 --> 01:00:31,169
that Papa had a stroke.

1353
01:00:31,252 --> 01:00:32,462
They took him to the hospital,

1354
01:00:32,545 --> 01:00:36,090
and I wasn't able to
go because I had work.

1355
01:00:36,174 --> 01:00:38,635
I was shocked. I was at work at the time.

1356
01:00:38,718 --> 01:00:40,261
I can't remember what I was working on,

1357
01:00:40,345 --> 01:00:44,515
I was in the middle of it,
so I couldn't function properly.

1358
01:00:44,599 --> 01:00:46,225
We messaged her, "What happened?"

1359
01:00:46,309 --> 01:00:47,602
And she wanted to
continue with the training.

1360
01:00:47,685 --> 01:00:52,815
- [somber music continues]
- Whoa!

1361
01:00:52,899 --> 01:00:55,777
Louder. One more time, let's go.

1362
01:00:55,860 --> 01:00:56,861
I couldn't hear.

1363
01:00:56,944 --> 01:00:58,946
His voice was so loud. It hurt.

1364
01:00:59,030 --> 01:01:00,573
Could you please tell them...

1365
01:01:00,657 --> 01:01:03,493
[Maloi] The voice
message my sibling received

1366
01:01:03,576 --> 01:01:04,619
was just a voice message.

1367
01:01:04,702 --> 01:01:06,204
He said,

1368
01:01:06,287 --> 01:01:09,582
"Where’s Mama? I can't move."

1369
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:14,003
Turns out he had a stroke.

1370
01:01:15,129 --> 01:01:17,548
I really cried for several days.

1371
01:01:17,632 --> 01:01:19,967
Because, you know,
my frustration from last time

1372
01:01:20,051 --> 01:01:23,304
was that no one would
greet me when I'd come home

1373
01:01:23,388 --> 01:01:26,015
Then I find out that Papa got sick.

1374
01:01:27,850 --> 01:01:32,897
[Mikha] Of course, when a parent of ours
gets sick or has a problem,

1375
01:01:32,980 --> 01:01:34,440
it affects all of us

1376
01:01:34,524 --> 01:01:36,984
because it feels like
they're also our moms and dads,

1377
01:01:37,068 --> 01:01:38,194
or something like that.

1378
01:01:38,277 --> 01:01:40,863
We worried about Maloi

1379
01:01:41,906 --> 01:01:43,032
because it's not...

1380
01:01:43,116 --> 01:01:45,034
It's not easy especially if it's family.

1381
01:01:45,118 --> 01:01:46,994
And then,

1382
01:01:47,078 --> 01:01:48,621
on top of all the training and fatigue,

1383
01:01:48,705 --> 01:01:52,333
I still have to think about it.
I'm training for what? For who?

1384
01:01:52,417 --> 01:01:53,668
A-And they're incomplete.

1385
01:01:53,751 --> 01:01:56,295
We were shocked to find
out she was just in the condo.

1386
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:57,880
Then she said she wasn't going home.

1387
01:01:57,964 --> 01:02:01,384
So we said, "Why? You need to go home

1388
01:02:01,467 --> 01:02:04,887
so at least you'll feel at
ease being by your dad’s side."

1389
01:02:04,971 --> 01:02:07,557
She really didn't want to,
despite all our insistence.

1390
01:02:07,640 --> 01:02:11,436
Because she wanted to distract herself

1391
01:02:11,519 --> 01:02:14,772
and didn't want to bother us
since the concert was coming up.

1392
01:02:14,856 --> 01:02:20,987
[somber music continues]

1393
01:02:21,070 --> 01:02:22,196
[Sheena] She chose to stay in training

1394
01:02:22,280 --> 01:02:26,367
because if you miss
even just one day of training

1395
01:02:26,451 --> 01:02:28,870
for the <i>Grand BINIverse,</i>
you'll miss so much.

1396
01:02:28,953 --> 01:02:31,622
Us girls, we felt bad because we thought,

1397
01:02:31,706 --> 01:02:35,126
"Oh no, maybe Maloi will get distracted."

1398
01:02:35,209 --> 01:02:37,044
Because of what happened with her dad,

1399
01:02:37,128 --> 01:02:38,921
she didn't know what to prioritize.

1400
01:02:39,005 --> 01:02:42,258
But it seems
she prefers having someone with her

1401
01:02:42,341 --> 01:02:43,593
rather than being alone.

1402
01:02:43,676 --> 01:02:46,262
So, we understood. Okay.

1403
01:02:46,345 --> 01:02:51,100
[somber music continues]

1404
01:02:51,184 --> 01:02:53,853
I went home for just one night,

1405
01:02:53,936 --> 01:02:54,812
he was already in the hospital.

1406
01:02:54,896 --> 01:02:57,482
He was so thin,

1407
01:02:57,565 --> 01:02:58,733
so restless.

1408
01:02:58,816 --> 01:02:59,984
He wasn't

1409
01:03:01,110 --> 01:03:04,405
the dad I was used to.

1410
01:03:04,489 --> 01:03:07,450
The doctor said that his brain

1411
01:03:07,533 --> 01:03:09,035
He had like a--

1412
01:03:09,118 --> 01:03:10,077
It's a--

1413
01:03:10,161 --> 01:03:12,038
He had some bleeding.

1414
01:03:12,121 --> 01:03:16,167
So when I had
the opportunity to go home, I went home.

1415
01:03:16,250 --> 01:03:19,212
I just spent that time with Papa.

1416
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:27,720
[Colet] I saw
that Maloi can handle herself well.

1417
01:03:27,804 --> 01:03:30,640
She's very
professional in everything she does.

1418
01:03:30,723 --> 01:03:33,184
[Mikha] We're proud of you, Maloi.

1419
01:03:33,267 --> 01:03:36,896
And we're so glad you pushed through it.

1420
01:03:36,979 --> 01:03:38,523
It definitely hasn't been easy.

1421
01:03:38,606 --> 01:03:42,276
I know how much your family means to you,

1422
01:03:42,360 --> 01:03:44,570
and I hope your dad gets well.

1423
01:03:44,654 --> 01:03:45,655
Yeah.

1424
01:03:49,992 --> 01:03:56,332
[thrilling music playing]

1425
01:03:56,415 --> 01:03:58,042
[crowd screaming]

1426
01:03:58,125 --> 01:04:01,003
[crowd chanting “ey”]

1427
01:04:07,468 --> 01:04:09,303
[Stacey] I think about the time

1428
01:04:09,387 --> 01:04:12,014
when I was lining up in
the parking lot of Araneta Coliseum,

1429
01:04:12,098 --> 01:04:14,559
with thousands of
others who were also dreaming.

1430
01:04:14,642 --> 01:04:16,853
We all shared
the same dream of getting in.

1431
01:04:19,939 --> 01:04:21,941
Mommy said she remembered,

1432
01:04:22,024 --> 01:04:24,652
we were just on the side, sitting down.

1433
01:04:24,735 --> 01:04:27,446
We didn't know what to do.

1434
01:04:27,530 --> 01:04:31,200
Then we were watching
the dancers, the ones auditioning.

1435
01:04:36,622 --> 01:04:38,374
[Stacey] From not knowing what to do

1436
01:04:38,457 --> 01:04:42,211
to having BINI's first-ever
concert at the Araneta Coliseum,

1437
01:04:42,295 --> 01:04:46,841
It’s just so amazing. Truly,
God aligned the stars for BINI.

1438
01:04:46,924 --> 01:04:49,760
[staff squealing]

1439
01:04:49,844 --> 01:04:53,264
[thrilling music continues]

1440
01:04:53,347 --> 01:04:54,515
[Colet] When we were still trainees,

1441
01:04:54,599 --> 01:04:58,227
we would just edit BINI,
put them on stage.

1442
01:04:58,311 --> 01:05:00,187
And that was
our phone wallpaper for months.

1443
01:05:00,271 --> 01:05:07,278
[thrilling music continues]

1444
01:05:09,113 --> 01:05:11,699
[Colet] So now
we really see that it’s happening.

1445
01:05:11,782 --> 01:05:14,285
The impact of
our <i>Grand BINIverse</i> is amazing

1446
01:05:14,368 --> 01:05:16,996
because we didn't know

1447
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:19,248
that it would happen this year.

1448
01:05:19,332 --> 01:05:21,125
Aah! Lord!

1449
01:05:21,208 --> 01:05:22,877
[Mickey] Jhoanna says it all the time,

1450
01:05:22,960 --> 01:05:23,961
"Araneta!"

1451
01:05:24,045 --> 01:05:25,755
Good luck, girls!

1452
01:05:25,838 --> 01:05:28,299
Because every artist here,

1453
01:05:28,382 --> 01:05:31,052
in OPM history,
they always talk about Araneta.

1454
01:05:31,135 --> 01:05:34,889
[thrilling music continues]

1455
01:05:34,972 --> 01:05:37,016
Let's go, let's go!

1456
01:05:37,099 --> 01:05:38,476
[music fades]

1457
01:05:38,559 --> 01:05:45,274
[flatline sfx]

1458
01:05:47,234 --> 01:05:52,657
- ["Pantropiko" by BINI playing]
- [crowd screaming, applauding]

1459
01:05:52,740 --> 01:05:56,118
[BINI singing]
<i>♪ Pantropiko, Pantropiko, oh ♪</i>

1460
01:05:58,245 --> 01:06:01,999
<i>Pantropiko, Pantropiko, oh</i>

1461
01:06:03,125 --> 01:06:05,962
<i>Pantropiko, Pantropiko, oh</i>

1462
01:06:07,129 --> 01:06:12,259
[BINI] Let me hear you say, B-I-N-I, BINI!

1463
01:06:12,343 --> 01:06:17,098
Everybody! B-I-N-I, BINI!

1464
01:06:17,181 --> 01:06:22,103
Louder! B-I-N-I, BINI!

1465
01:06:22,186 --> 01:06:27,400
One more time! B-I-N-I, BINI!

1466
01:06:28,317 --> 01:06:30,236
[Lauren] With all the light sticks-- Wow,

1467
01:06:30,319 --> 01:06:34,365
it looked beautiful,
they were surrounded by stars all around.

1468
01:06:34,448 --> 01:06:37,159
It was quite an achievement.

1469
01:06:37,243 --> 01:06:41,414
<i>I saw you At an unexpected time</i>

1470
01:06:41,497 --> 01:06:46,502
<i>You came suddenly
As if it was no coincidence</i>

1471
01:06:46,585 --> 01:06:49,296
<i>Is this fate?</i>

1472
01:06:49,380 --> 01:06:52,591
If you're there and
you can even be closer,

1473
01:06:52,675 --> 01:06:55,511
it gives them a different feeling,

1474
01:06:55,594 --> 01:06:57,013
that you’re reaching out to them

1475
01:06:57,096 --> 01:06:58,931
and you're even closer to them.

1476
01:06:59,015 --> 01:07:01,142
Because I’ve realized
and I keep on telling them,

1477
01:07:01,225 --> 01:07:04,437
“Girls, every time you perform,

1478
01:07:04,520 --> 01:07:06,981
one smile from
you means the world to everyone.”

1479
01:07:07,064 --> 01:07:11,235
<i>What is this that I'm feeling?
Oh, shocks, is this love?</i>

1480
01:07:11,318 --> 01:07:12,528
<i>Is what I'm feeling for real?</i>

1481
01:07:12,611 --> 01:07:14,488
[Maloi] So during <i>Karera,</i> right?

1482
01:07:14,572 --> 01:07:17,033
We were in the cart...

1483
01:07:17,116 --> 01:07:19,744
<i>Every day, I feel happier</i>

1484
01:07:19,827 --> 01:07:23,372
<i>Ever since I saw
you The worries are fading away</i>

1485
01:07:23,456 --> 01:07:26,167
[Maloi] At that time,
he stood at the side of the stairs,

1486
01:07:26,250 --> 01:07:27,585
and that's when I cried so much

1487
01:07:27,668 --> 01:07:29,628
because I didn't
know he was going to watch.

1488
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:32,548
I was just so happy because...

1489
01:07:37,136 --> 01:07:39,764
even though he was sick,

1490
01:07:39,847 --> 01:07:41,474
he still came.

1491
01:07:41,557 --> 01:07:47,563
["Pantropiko" continues]

1492
01:07:48,439 --> 01:07:50,983
[Lauren] A lot has been posted on TikTok

1493
01:07:51,067 --> 01:07:53,611
and various social media platforms

1494
01:07:53,694 --> 01:07:57,364
about how <i>BINI</i>,
the girls, and <i>BINI's</i> music

1495
01:07:57,448 --> 01:08:00,868
have affected many people
during their most challenging times.

1496
01:08:00,951 --> 01:08:01,869
It got to a point where

1497
01:08:01,952 --> 01:08:03,913
I didn't know what I was fighting for.

1498
01:08:03,996 --> 01:08:05,915
I didn't know what
life I was fighting for.

1499
01:08:05,998 --> 01:08:08,793
But because of <i>BINI</i> and their songs,

1500
01:08:08,876 --> 01:08:10,753
I was reminded
that maybe it's not too late

1501
01:08:10,836 --> 01:08:12,755
to try for my dreams again.

1502
01:08:12,838 --> 01:08:16,717
Maybe I guess I'll try again,
maybe life's still worth living.

1503
01:08:20,721 --> 01:08:23,349
[Sheena] And then,
when I looked up, the place was packed.

1504
01:08:23,432 --> 01:08:24,767
It was so beautiful, I thought,

1505
01:08:24,850 --> 01:08:28,062
maybe it would've been
better if Mommy was here watching.

1506
01:08:29,271 --> 01:08:32,691
Because she never
got to see me in <i>BINI</i> at all.

1507
01:08:39,490 --> 01:08:42,743
She didn't get to see <i>BINI</i> Sheena,

1508
01:08:42,827 --> 01:08:44,245
and that was her dream.

1509
01:08:44,328 --> 01:08:48,707
Mommy was a huge
KPOP fan, so if she saw me,

1510
01:08:48,791 --> 01:08:49,917
she'd be so proud.

1511
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:51,418
And if she were still here,

1512
01:08:51,502 --> 01:08:53,212
she would've watched the whole three days.

1513
01:08:57,925 --> 01:08:59,635
It was so beautiful.
I'm getting teary-eyed.

1514
01:08:59,718 --> 01:09:01,762
Maybe if the concert
wasn't good, I wouldn't cry.

1515
01:09:01,846 --> 01:09:04,431
It would've been like,
"It's okay, if you missed this,

1516
01:09:04,515 --> 01:09:05,766
it wasn't good anyway."

1517
01:09:05,850 --> 01:09:06,684
But it was beautiful.

1518
01:09:08,727 --> 01:09:10,396
[Lauren] You're not just performers,

1519
01:09:10,479 --> 01:09:11,939
you are a source of inspiration.

1520
01:09:12,022 --> 01:09:14,024
That's enough reason for you

1521
01:09:14,108 --> 01:09:17,111
to give your 100% performing on stage.

1522
01:09:17,194 --> 01:09:19,071
[coach Mickey] To be <i>BINI,</i>
you have to be involved.

1523
01:09:19,155 --> 01:09:20,865
You have to share
your opinion and your heart.

1524
01:09:20,948 --> 01:09:24,243
Is it a heartbreak,
is it pain, or whatever?

1525
01:09:24,326 --> 01:09:26,662
This all matters to become an artist.

1526
01:09:26,745 --> 01:09:30,666
So now I see that they're maturing more.

1527
01:09:30,749 --> 01:09:33,169
Their voice is now
very important to everyone.

1528
01:09:38,716 --> 01:09:40,718
[Jonathan] Through
the music of <i>BINI</i> right now,

1529
01:09:40,801 --> 01:09:44,597
we've encapsulated
the pop culture of today.

1530
01:09:44,680 --> 01:09:47,183
This is the music I danced to,
the one we sang at graduation...

1531
01:09:47,266 --> 01:09:50,394
those kinds of
memories are embedded forever.

1532
01:09:52,563 --> 01:09:56,150
[Corey] The <i>BINI</i> girls
are very, very good women.

1533
01:09:56,233 --> 01:09:58,152
Their advocacies are noble.

1534
01:09:58,235 --> 01:10:04,742
And they incorporate that in their music,
from self love to mental health.

1535
01:10:04,825 --> 01:10:07,786
And when they believe in something,

1536
01:10:07,870 --> 01:10:09,955
they really stand by that.

1537
01:10:11,707 --> 01:10:13,125
[Carlo] What <i>BINI</i> represents

1538
01:10:13,209 --> 01:10:16,879
is the unlimited
potential for Filipino talent to shine.

1539
01:10:16,962 --> 01:10:19,506
I'd like to think <i>BINI</i> opened the doors

1540
01:10:19,590 --> 01:10:22,051
for many other Filipino artists

1541
01:10:22,134 --> 01:10:24,511
to be recognized globally.

1542
01:10:24,595 --> 01:10:26,055
[Roxy] Making music

1543
01:10:26,138 --> 01:10:27,848
should touch the heart of the Filipinos.

1544
01:10:27,932 --> 01:10:29,850
That's what's very important for us.

1545
01:10:33,145 --> 01:10:34,647
[coach Mickey] What they did right now,

1546
01:10:34,730 --> 01:10:36,232
seeing their hard work and discipline,

1547
01:10:36,315 --> 01:10:39,610
and talent and where it can lead,

1548
01:10:39,693 --> 01:10:41,862
I think that's the legacy
that they are doing already now

1549
01:10:41,946 --> 01:10:43,489
for the next generation.

1550
01:10:43,572 --> 01:10:45,199
That will last forever,

1551
01:10:45,282 --> 01:10:48,244
because I think that's
the change we needed.

1552
01:10:48,327 --> 01:10:49,536
[Lauren] As they carry

1553
01:10:49,620 --> 01:10:52,248
the banner of the Philippines
to the international arena,

1554
01:10:52,331 --> 01:10:55,292
the <i>Blooms</i> will still be
with them on that journey.

1555
01:10:58,045 --> 01:11:01,590
Nothing is impossible, we can dream big,

1556
01:11:01,674 --> 01:11:05,511
and we can really aspire to be bigger than

1557
01:11:05,594 --> 01:11:08,138
what we thought we could do.

1558
01:11:08,222 --> 01:11:10,349
[audience cheering, applauding]

1559
01:11:23,237 --> 01:11:24,446
[Gwen] Infinity.

1560
01:11:24,530 --> 01:11:27,283
It reminds me of the time when we started.

1561
01:11:27,366 --> 01:11:31,078
We were so young
when we first did this hand sign,

1562
01:11:31,161 --> 01:11:34,373
and having something like that

1563
01:11:34,456 --> 01:11:37,626
made us feel like we're getting there.

1564
01:11:37,710 --> 01:11:39,086
Like, we're about to debut--

1565
01:11:39,169 --> 01:11:40,462
I mean, we trained for a long time.

1566
01:11:40,546 --> 01:11:43,799
Even though the figure was repetitive,

1567
01:11:43,882 --> 01:11:48,137
it means that the eight
of us all dreamed together,

1568
01:11:48,220 --> 01:11:51,307
and little by little,
we achieved our dreams.

1569
01:11:51,390 --> 01:11:53,517
We come from different backgrounds,

1570
01:11:53,600 --> 01:11:56,353
but we all meet at a certain point.

1571
01:11:56,437 --> 01:11:59,189
We went through a lot together,

1572
01:11:59,273 --> 01:12:01,734
and at the same time,
we are still growing.

1573
01:12:01,817 --> 01:12:03,319
We are continuously growing.

1574
01:12:03,402 --> 01:12:05,779
We are never stagnant for a long time.

1575
01:12:05,863 --> 01:12:10,034
We are always willing to
get to know each other more

1576
01:12:10,117 --> 01:12:13,203
and willing to
connect with each other more.

1577
01:12:13,287 --> 01:12:14,705
It's not just the good times,

1578
01:12:14,788 --> 01:12:18,751
we're also there for
each other during bad times.

1579
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:22,671
Of course,
they have their own struggles too,

1580
01:12:22,755 --> 01:12:25,132
but I know I can always count on them,

1581
01:12:25,215 --> 01:12:26,633
and I'm so grateful for that.

1582
01:12:26,717 --> 01:12:28,719
BINI still has a long way to go,

1583
01:12:28,802 --> 01:12:31,597
and I know we'll achieve so much more.

1584
01:12:31,680 --> 01:12:35,726
Like I said,
I'm excited to grow old with them.

1585
01:12:35,809 --> 01:12:38,228
And our goal is to
have kids together, right?

1586
01:12:38,312 --> 01:12:39,646
[chuckles]

1587
01:12:39,730 --> 01:12:41,732
It's engraved in me. It's like a tattoo.

1588
01:12:41,815 --> 01:12:46,362
It has been my life.
It's part of my blood.

1589
01:12:46,445 --> 01:12:48,030
Who I am and who I will be...

1590
01:12:48,113 --> 01:12:52,076
It's because I was a BINI
that made me who I will be.

1591
01:12:52,159 --> 01:12:54,703
Our love for each other is endless.

1592
01:12:54,787 --> 01:12:55,913
It's infinite.

1593
01:12:55,996 --> 01:13:00,626
We will treasure
our memories, our moments together,

1594
01:13:00,709 --> 01:13:05,047
the struggles,
the laughter, and the tears.

1595
01:13:05,130 --> 01:13:07,674
We'll treasure it forever.

1596
01:13:07,758 --> 01:13:09,510
I love them so much.

1597
01:13:09,593 --> 01:13:11,929
Aww. Uh...

1598
01:13:12,012 --> 01:13:13,347
Eight until the end.

1599
01:13:13,430 --> 01:13:16,392
That's what we hold on to,
that no one will give up.

1600
01:13:16,475 --> 01:13:18,936
There's still a lot of
people we can inspire,

1601
01:13:19,019 --> 01:13:22,064
and we have a long
journey ahead as a group.

1602
01:13:23,941 --> 01:13:26,235
["Na Na Na" by BINI playing]

1603
01:13:26,318 --> 01:13:28,695
[Sheena] Wow,
our leader is booked and busy.

1604
01:13:28,779 --> 01:13:30,239
She's doing so many things.

1605
01:13:30,322 --> 01:13:32,241
But it's not like she was forced into it.

1606
01:13:32,324 --> 01:13:34,410
She does everything because she wants to.

1607
01:13:34,493 --> 01:13:36,328
[Colet] Twenty four hours isn't enough

1608
01:13:36,412 --> 01:13:38,956
for her to do everything she wants to do.

1609
01:13:39,039 --> 01:13:41,625
[Maloi] I'm so proud
to see her handling it all,

1610
01:13:41,708 --> 01:13:44,253
and that she takes
care of us like her sisters

1611
01:13:44,336 --> 01:13:45,754
even though we're older than her.

1612
01:13:45,838 --> 01:13:47,798
Is that true?
They're just trying to flatter me.

1613
01:13:47,881 --> 01:13:50,426
Being a leader also means
being able to follow your members

1614
01:13:50,509 --> 01:13:51,844
and listening to them.

1615
01:13:51,927 --> 01:13:53,345
[screaming]

1616
01:13:53,429 --> 01:13:55,973
[overlapping chatter]

1617
01:13:56,056 --> 01:14:00,686
[Mikha] Aiah
focused on herself a lot more.

1618
01:14:00,769 --> 01:14:03,439
She really tried to
build herself up from that.

1619
01:14:03,522 --> 01:14:06,984
She has found
her happiness and what she wants to do.

1620
01:14:07,067 --> 01:14:08,444
When Aiah isn't around,

1621
01:14:08,527 --> 01:14:10,904
it feels like our day isn't complete

1622
01:14:10,988 --> 01:14:12,614
because we don't
have anyone to laugh with.

1623
01:14:12,698 --> 01:14:15,242
She's naturally funny, too.

1624
01:14:15,325 --> 01:14:18,162
[Aiah] Based on my dad's words,

1625
01:14:18,245 --> 01:14:19,663
it felt like I just played around,

1626
01:14:19,746 --> 01:14:22,291
which is actually a good thing.

1627
01:14:22,374 --> 01:14:23,250
I just enjoyed myself.

1628
01:14:24,543 --> 01:14:26,086
[Jhoanna] She's not "Anger" anymore.

1629
01:14:26,170 --> 01:14:28,464
So when I see
tweets about her being angry,

1630
01:14:28,547 --> 01:14:30,132
I want to reply and say,

1631
01:14:30,215 --> 01:14:33,260
"Hey, remove that image of Colet,

1632
01:14:33,343 --> 01:14:34,720
she's really changed now."

1633
01:14:34,803 --> 01:14:37,222
She said, "They were
the ones who said I was always angry,

1634
01:14:37,306 --> 01:14:39,183
and now they're mad at me." [chuckles]

1635
01:14:40,309 --> 01:14:43,937
[Aiah] She is joy,
sadness, and even anxiety.

1636
01:14:44,021 --> 01:14:47,024
And it turns out she's just
like everyone else. She's human.

1637
01:14:47,107 --> 01:14:48,901
She experiences all those emotions.

1638
01:14:48,984 --> 01:14:50,944
[Colet] I really
enjoyed the <i>Grand BINIverse.</i>

1639
01:14:51,028 --> 01:14:54,531
My goal was just to smile and smile.

1640
01:14:54,615 --> 01:14:57,534
[Maloi] Stacey's
growth this year is also incredible.

1641
01:14:57,618 --> 01:15:00,037
She really bloomed this year.

1642
01:15:00,120 --> 01:15:02,164
She found what's perfect for her.

1643
01:15:02,247 --> 01:15:04,833
[Sheena] I also see that she's really

1644
01:15:04,917 --> 01:15:06,752
fighting for her confidence,

1645
01:15:06,835 --> 01:15:09,171
and once she finds it, that's it.

1646
01:15:09,254 --> 01:15:10,380
She's slaying it.

1647
01:15:10,464 --> 01:15:15,552
She's able to show
her natural self on camera.

1648
01:15:16,345 --> 01:15:19,556
[Colet] With Gwen, you can see her growth

1649
01:15:19,640 --> 01:15:21,767
when she tries new things that scare her.

1650
01:15:21,850 --> 01:15:25,103
She's really out there facing her fears.

1651
01:15:25,187 --> 01:15:27,314
[Mikha] Gwen is also one of my babies,

1652
01:15:27,397 --> 01:15:28,941
even though she is older than me.

1653
01:15:29,024 --> 01:15:32,903
She may seem quiet and shy,
but when it's just us two,

1654
01:15:32,986 --> 01:15:34,821
she'll talk your ears off.

1655
01:15:34,905 --> 01:15:38,116
Gwen was so extra
during the <i>Grand BINIverse.</i>

1656
01:15:38,200 --> 01:15:39,409
She was so extra.

1657
01:15:39,493 --> 01:15:42,871
[Gwen] It was the first
time all of my family got to watch.

1658
01:15:42,955 --> 01:15:47,751
I felt very inspired to
perform since my family was there.

1659
01:15:49,294 --> 01:15:52,422
[Sheena] With Maloi, seeing her okay,

1660
01:15:52,506 --> 01:15:54,383
and that she's fighting makes me happy.

1661
01:15:54,466 --> 01:15:58,470
And it warms my heart to
see that she's managing all this.

1662
01:15:58,554 --> 01:16:02,599
[Stacey] I admire
how skilled she is in her art,

1663
01:16:02,683 --> 01:16:06,103
her style, and how smart she thinks.

1664
01:16:06,186 --> 01:16:09,648
[Maloi] I'm super
grateful that I am emotionally stable.

1665
01:16:09,731 --> 01:16:14,319
I'm mentally stable,
despite what happened to my father.

1666
01:16:14,403 --> 01:16:17,531
I don't want to! I might cry if I do.

1667
01:16:18,865 --> 01:16:21,368
[Colet] Sheena is so mature now.

1668
01:16:21,451 --> 01:16:24,413
But no matter what,
she listens to us, her sisters.

1669
01:16:24,496 --> 01:16:27,457
[Gwen] She just
keeps getting better and better.

1670
01:16:27,541 --> 01:16:30,669
She's more agile, and more energetic.

1671
01:16:30,752 --> 01:16:32,379
I don't know why she's like that.

1672
01:16:32,462 --> 01:16:35,632
They say the older you get,
the less energy you have.

1673
01:16:35,716 --> 01:16:36,883
But it's the opposite for her.

1674
01:16:36,967 --> 01:16:41,013
Even if she wants to be joyful,
and she wants us to be happy,

1675
01:16:41,096 --> 01:16:46,018
it's also okay to
open up the sadness to us.

1676
01:16:46,101 --> 01:16:48,812
[Sheena] I grew up. I'm 20 years old.

1677
01:16:48,895 --> 01:16:50,689
There are no more teens in BINI.

1678
01:16:50,772 --> 01:16:53,942
The girls used to say that if
we're not teenagers anymore,

1679
01:16:54,026 --> 01:16:56,361
or once I turn 20,
that means we're getting old.

1680
01:16:56,445 --> 01:17:00,949
That's what changed in me.
I want to improve my dancing.

1681
01:17:01,033 --> 01:17:02,200
I want to dance really good, you know?

1682
01:17:02,284 --> 01:17:06,496
[Aiah] People know
Mikha as the nonchalant one.

1683
01:17:06,580 --> 01:17:09,207
But she's really extra, too.
She's super extra.

1684
01:17:09,291 --> 01:17:14,296
[Jhoanna] I noticed
her growth and how she's opening up more.

1685
01:17:14,379 --> 01:17:16,340
I noticed how Mikha
started to enjoy things more,

1686
01:17:16,423 --> 01:17:18,759
and she's more vocal
about her love for BINI.

1687
01:17:18,842 --> 01:17:21,345
I don't know why,
but she wasn't like that before.

1688
01:17:21,428 --> 01:17:25,307
She told us how being in
BINI is one of her life's highlights.

1689
01:17:25,390 --> 01:17:28,894
I was surprised to hear
Mikha say something like that.

1690
01:17:28,977 --> 01:17:30,729
It's fate.

1691
01:17:30,812 --> 01:17:32,230
Corny, right?

1692
01:17:32,314 --> 01:17:37,444
Fate brought us all together,
and how everything is happening.

1693
01:17:37,527 --> 01:17:39,905
But I'm sure this will be a long journey.

1694
01:17:39,988 --> 01:17:43,909
It's a big accomplishment
to be known in the Philippines.

1695
01:17:43,992 --> 01:17:46,495
But to be known worldwide?
That's another story.

1696
01:17:46,578 --> 01:17:51,249
And that's another story that we will tell
in the next chapter.

1697
01:17:51,833 --> 01:17:57,964
["Na Na Na" by BINI playing]

1698
01:18:11,645 --> 01:18:15,065
This is BINI Jhoanna.
Two, three, thank you!

1699
01:18:15,148 --> 01:18:17,442
["Huwag Muna
Tayong Umuwi" by BINI playing]

1700
01:18:17,526 --> 01:18:18,443
Bye.

1701
01:18:18,527 --> 01:18:22,489
Hi guys, I'm Mikha. Two, three, thank you!

1702
01:18:22,572 --> 01:18:24,282
What did the other girls say?

1703
01:18:24,366 --> 01:18:28,078
Hi, I'm BINI Stacey.
Two, three, thank you!

1704
01:18:28,161 --> 01:18:29,079
This one?

1705
01:18:29,162 --> 01:18:33,458
Hi guys, I'm BINI Gwen.
Two, three, thank you!

1706
01:18:33,542 --> 01:18:36,378
- Aah! Oh, there's more.
- Last one, Maloi.

1707
01:18:36,461 --> 01:18:40,674
Hi everyone, I'm Maloi from BINI.

1708
01:18:40,757 --> 01:18:43,051
Two, three, thank you!

1709
01:18:43,135 --> 01:18:46,763
I'm BINI Colet. Two, three, thank you!

1710
01:18:46,847 --> 01:18:49,141
Eyy!

1711
01:18:49,224 --> 01:18:53,145
Hi, I'm BINI Sheena.
Two, three, thank you!

1712
01:18:53,228 --> 01:18:55,897
Who's your bias? [laughter]

1713
01:18:55,981 --> 01:19:00,026
Hi, I'm BINI Aiah. Two, three, thank you!

1714
01:19:00,110 --> 01:19:07,117
["Huwag Muna
Tayong Umuwi" by BINI continues]
